window.LEETCODE_NOTES = {"generatedAt":"local","notes":[{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Bitmask/1434._Number_of_Ways_to_Wear_Different_Hats_to_Each_Other.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Bitmask/1434._Number_of_Ways_to_Wear_Different_Hats_to_Each_Other.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Bitmask","title":"1434. Number of Ways to Wear Different Hats to Each Other.md","displayTitle":"1434. Number of Ways to Wear Different Hats to Each Other","problemNumber":1434,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1434. Number of Ways to Wear Different Hats to Each Other.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def numberWays(self, hats: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        h2p = defaultdict(list)  \n        for i, hat in enumerate(hats):  \n            for h in hat:  \n                h2p[h].append(i)  \n        n = len(hats)  \n\n        @lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(hat, mask):  \n            if mask == 0: return 1  \n            if hat < 1: return 0  \n              \n            ret = dp(hat-1, mask)  \n            for p in h2p[hat]:  \n                if mask & (1 << p):  \n                    mask ^= (1 << p)  \n                    ret += dp(hat-1, mask)  \n                    mask |= (1 << p)  \n            return ret % (10**9 + 7)  \n          \n        return dp(40, (1<<n)-1)  \n```\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Bitmask/README.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Bitmask/README.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Bitmask","title":"Bitmask Overview","displayTitle":"Bitmask Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/120._Triangle.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/120._Triangle.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"120. Triangle.md","displayTitle":"120. Triangle","problemNumber":120,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"120. Triangle.md\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/139._Word_Break.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/139._Word_Break.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"139. Word Break.md","displayTitle":"139. Word Break","problemNumber":139,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/word-break/discuss/665575/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"139. Word Break.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/word-break/discuss/665575/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/140._Word_Break_II.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/140._Word_Break_II.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"140. Word Break II.md","displayTitle":"140. Word Break II","problemNumber":140,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/word-break-ii/discuss/672708/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"140. Word Break II.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/word-break-ii/discuss/672708/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/152._Maximum_Product_Subarray.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/152._Maximum_Product_Subarray.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"152. Maximum Product Subarray.md","displayTitle":"152. Maximum Product Subarray","problemNumber":152,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-subarray/discuss/665622/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"152. Maximum Product Subarray.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-subarray/discuss/665622/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/198._House_Robber.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/198._House_Robber.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"198. House Robber.md","displayTitle":"198. House Robber","problemNumber":198,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"198. House Robber.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def rob(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:  \n        if not nums: return 0  \n        '''  \n        # bottom up  \n        a, b = 0, nums[0]  \n        for v in nums[1:]:  \n            a, b = b, max(b, a+v)  \n        return b  \n        '''  \n        # Top down  \n        d = {-1: 0, 0: nums[0]}  \n        def helper(k):  \n            if k in d: return d[k]  \n            d[k] = max(helper(k-2)+nums[k], helper(k-1))  \n            return d[k]  \n        return helper(len(nums)-1)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/264._Ugly_Number_II.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/264._Ugly_Number_II.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"264. Ugly Number II.md","displayTitle":"264. Ugly Number II","problemNumber":264,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"264. Ugly Number II.md\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/279._Perfect_Squares.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/279._Perfect_Squares.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"279. Perfect Squares.md","displayTitle":"279. Perfect Squares","problemNumber":279,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"279. Perfect Squares.md\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/309._Best_Time_to_Buy_and_Sell_Stock_with_Cooldown.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/309._Best_Time_to_Buy_and_Sell_Stock_with_Cooldown.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"309. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock with Cooldown.md","displayTitle":"309. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock with Cooldown","problemNumber":309,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-with-cooldown/discuss/669064/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"309. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock with Cooldown.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-with-cooldown/discuss/669064/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/32._Longest_Valid_Parentheses.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/32._Longest_Valid_Parentheses.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"32. Longest Valid Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"32. Longest Valid Parentheses","problemNumber":32,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-valid-parentheses/discuss/669186/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"32. Longest Valid Parentheses.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/longest-valid-parentheses/discuss/669186/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/338._Counting_Bits.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/338._Counting_Bits.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"338. Counting Bits.md","displayTitle":"338. Counting Bits","problemNumber":338,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"338. Counting Bits.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def countBits(self, num: int) -> List[int]:  \n        dp = [0] * (num+1)  \n        if num == 0: return dp  \n        dp[1], prev = 1, 1  \n        for i in range(2, num+1):  \n            if i == prev * 2:  \n                dp[i] = 1  \n                prev = i  \n            else:  \n                dp[i] = 1 + dp[i-prev]  \n        return dp  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/343._Integer_Break.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/343._Integer_Break.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"343. Integer Break.md","displayTitle":"343. Integer Break","problemNumber":343,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/integer-break/discuss/676483/Python-DP-without-math-trick"],"markdown":"343. Integer Break.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/integer-break/discuss/676483/Python-DP-without-math-trick\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/357._Count_Numbers_with_Unique_Digits.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/357._Count_Numbers_with_Unique_Digits.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"357. Count Numbers with Unique Digits.md","displayTitle":"357. Count Numbers with Unique Digits","problemNumber":357,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"357. Count Numbers with Unique Digits.md\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/413._Arithmetic_Slices.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/413._Arithmetic_Slices.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"413. Arithmetic Slices.md","displayTitle":"413. Arithmetic Slices","problemNumber":413,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/arithmetic-slices/discuss/671064/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"413. Arithmetic Slices.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/arithmetic-slices/discuss/671064/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/472._Concatenated_Words.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/472._Concatenated_Words.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"472. Concatenated Words.md","displayTitle":"472. Concatenated Words","problemNumber":472,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"472. Concatenated Words.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findAllConcatenatedWordsInADict(self, words: List[str]) -> List[str]:  \n        # Top down DP: Time  O(N * M^2) where M is the average length of the words  \n        #              Space O(N * M)  \n        d = set(words)  \n        import functools  \n        @functools.lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(word):  \n            if not word: return False  \n            return any((word[i:] in d) and (word[:i] in d or dp(word[:i])) for i in range(1, len(word)))  \n        return [word for word in words if dp(word)]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/64._Minimum_Path_Sum.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/64._Minimum_Path_Sum.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"64. Minimum Path Sum.md","displayTitle":"64. Minimum Path Sum","problemNumber":64,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-path-sum/discuss/667483/Python-Concise-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"64. Minimum Path Sum.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-path-sum/discuss/667483/Python-Concise-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/70._Climbing_Stairs.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/70._Climbing_Stairs.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"70. Climbing Stairs.md","displayTitle":"70. Climbing Stairs","problemNumber":70,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"70. Climbing Stairs.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def climbStairs(self, n: int) -> int:  \n        '''          \n        d = {0:1, 1:1}  \n        def helper(k):  \n            if k in d: return d[k]  \n            d[k] = helper(k-1) + helper(k-2)  \n            return d[k]  \n        return helper(n)  \n        '''  \n        a, b = 1, 1  \n        if n == 1: return 1  \n        while n > 1:  \n            a, b = b, a+b  \n            n-=1  \n        return b  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/894._All_Possible_Full_Binary_Trees.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/894._All_Possible_Full_Binary_Trees.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"894. All Possible Full Binary Trees.md","displayTitle":"894. All Possible Full Binary Trees","problemNumber":894,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/all-possible-full-binary-trees/discuss/725016/Python-Concise-DP-Top-down-%2B-Bottom-up"],"markdown":"894. All Possible Full Binary Trees.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/all-possible-full-binary-trees/discuss/725016/Python-Concise-DP-Top-down-%2B-Bottom-up](https://leetcode.com/problems/all-possible-full-binary-trees/discuss/725016/Python-Concise-DP-Top-down-%2B-Bottom-up)\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/91._Decode_Ways.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/91._Decode_Ways.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"91. Decode Ways.md","displayTitle":"91. Decode Ways","problemNumber":91,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"91. Decode Ways.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def numDecodings(self, s: str) -> int:  \n        '''  \n        # Top down: Time O(N) Space O(N)  \n        dp = {0: 1}  \n        def helper(x):  \n            if x in dp: return dp[x]  \n            dp[x] = (helper(x-1) if s[x-1] != '0' else 0) + (helper(x-2) if x > 1 and 9 < int(s[x-2:x]) <= 26 else 0)  \n            return dp[x]  \n        return helper(len(s))  \n        '''  \n        # Bottom up: Time O(N) Space O(1)  \n        p2, p1 = 1, 1 if s[0] != '0' else 0  \n        for i in range(1, len(s)):  \n            cur = p1 if s[i] != '0' else 0  \n            cur += p2 if 9 < int(s[i-1:i+1]) <= 26 else 0  \n            if cur == 0: return 0  \n            p2, p1 = p1, cur  \n        return p1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/96._Unique_Binary_Search_Trees.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/96._Unique_Binary_Search_Trees.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"96. Unique Binary Search Trees.md","displayTitle":"96. Unique Binary Search Trees","problemNumber":96,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-binary-search-trees/discuss/665520/Python-Concise-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"96. Unique Binary Search Trees.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/unique-binary-search-trees/discuss/665520/Python-Concise-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/README.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/One-dimension/README.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"One dimension","title":"One dimension Overview","displayTitle":"One dimension Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/README.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/README.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Overview","title":"[MIT 6.006 Introduction to Algorithms, Fall 2011]([https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3P3cZGn6p661AmJdHafLMLzPxy5CXy-i](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3P3cZGn6p661AmJdHafLMLzPxy5CXy-i))","displayTitle":"Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":3,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/regular-expression-matching/discuss/665501/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down","https://leetcode.com/problems/wildcard-matching/discuss/687707/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down","https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3P3cZGn6p661AmJdHafLMLzPxy5CXy-i"],"markdown":"README.md\n[MIT 6.006 Introduction to Algorithms, Fall 2011]([https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3P3cZGn6p661AmJdHafLMLzPxy5CXy-i](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3P3cZGn6p661AmJdHafLMLzPxy5CXy-i))\n\n> Idea  \n\n1. DP is a smart brute force. It remember state while exhausting all possible cases.  \n2. DP is a DFS. Switching to BFS when it is too slow or taking too much memory to do DFS.  \n3. Transformation formula is the key of DP. `Bottom up` or `Top down` is just the implementation technical.   \n4. `Bottom up` implementation can be used to save memory when we only need states from last n levels.  \n5. Pay attention to edge cases. Edge cases used to happen when each parameter(dimension variable) reaching 0.   \n  E.g. 10. Regular Expression Matching  \n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isMatch(self, s: str, p: str) -> bool:  \n        # Memorization: Time O(M*N) Space O(M*N)  \n        m, n = len(s), len(p)  \n        import functools  \n        @functools.lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(x, y):  \n            if y == 0: return x == 0  \n            if x == 0: return y == 0 or y>=2 and p[y-1] == '*' and dp(x, y-2)  \n            if p[y-1] != '*':  \n                return p[y-1] in [s[x-1], '.'] and dp(x-1, y-1)  \n            else:  \n                return y>1 and (dp(x, y-2) or p[y-2] in [s[x-1], '.'] and dp(x-1, y))  \n        return dp(m, n)  \n```  \n\n6. Same idea when dealing contest/competitive games. Find the optimal move by exhausting all possible choice.   \n```python  \nDP(n) = max(Profit(move) - DP(move/next_start_point)  for move in possible_moves)  \n```  \n\n> Useful trick  \n\n\n1. `dict` can be more flexible compare to `array` since you can switch between `i`, `i+1`, `i-1` as needed when dealing edge cases.  \n2. Use tuple as key when multiple dimension dictionary/array is needed.   \n\n```python  \ndp = {}  \n# 1-d  \ndp[0] = 10  \n# 2-d  \ndp[0, 0] = 10  \n# 3-d  \ndp[0,0,0] = 10  \n```  \n\n3. `@lru_cache(None)` can be used for `Top down` implementation.  \n4. `State transformation formular` can be identical between `bottom up` and `top down` approach if we use variable carfully.  \n\n    > [10. Regular Expression Matching]([https://leetcode.com/problems/regular-expression-matching/discuss/665501/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down](https://leetcode.com/problems/regular-expression-matching/discuss/665501/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down))\n    > [44. Wildcard Matching]([https://leetcode.com/problems/wildcard-matching/discuss/687707/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down](https://leetcode.com/problems/wildcard-matching/discuss/687707/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down))\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Three-dimension/1463._Cherry_Pickup_II.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Three-dimension/1463._Cherry_Pickup_II.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Three dimension","title":"1463. Cherry Pickup II.md","displayTitle":"1463. Cherry Pickup II","problemNumber":1463,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1463. Cherry Pickup II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def cherryPickup(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        m, n = len(grid), len(grid[0])  \n          \n        @lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(row, r1, r2):  \n            if row == m: return 0  \n              \n            ret = collected = grid[row][r1] + (grid[row][r2] if r2 != r1 else 0)  \n            for i in range(-1, 2):  \n                if not 0 <= r1 + i < n: continue  \n                for j in range(-1, 2):  \n                    if not 0 <= r2 + j < n: continue  \n                    ret = max(ret, collected + dp(row+1, r1+i, r2+j))  \n              \n            return ret  \n          \n        return dp(0, 0, n-1)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Three-dimension/1473._Paint_House_III.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Three-dimension/1473._Paint_House_III.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Three dimension","title":"1473. Paint House III.md","displayTitle":"1473. Paint House III","problemNumber":1473,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/paint-house-iii/discuss/674485/Python-Solution"],"markdown":"1473. Paint House III.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/paint-house-iii/discuss/674485/Python-Solution](https://leetcode.com/problems/paint-house-iii/discuss/674485/Python-Solution)\n\t\n```python  \n\nclass Solution:  \n    def minCost(self, houses: List[int], cost: List[List[int]], m: int, n: int, target: int) -> int:  \n        '''  \n        # Top down: Time O(m*n*t*n) Space O(m*n*t)  \n        dp = {}# idx, t, color  \n        def helper(x, t, c):  \n            if (x, t ,c) in dp: return dp[x, t, c]  \n            if x < t or t < 1 or x < 0: return float('inf')  \n            my_cost = cost[x][c] if houses[x] == 0 else (0 if houses[x] == c+1 else float('inf'))  \n            if x == 0 and t == 1: return my_cost  \n            dp[x, t, c] = helper(x-1, t, c) + my_cost  \n            for i in range(n):  \n                if i == c: continue  \n                dp[x, t, c] = min(dp[x, t, c], helper(x-1, t-1, i)+my_cost)  \n            return dp[x, t, c]  \n        rst = min(helper(m-1, target, c) for c in range(n))  \n        return rst if rst != float('inf') else -1  \n        '''  \n        # Bottom up: Time O(m*n*t*n) Space O(n*t)  \n        dp, ndp = {(0,0): 0}, {} # (color, group)  \n        for i, c in enumerate(houses):  \n            for cc in (range(1, n+1) if c == 0 else [c]):  \n                for c_prev, g_prev in dp:  \n                    g_new = g_prev + (cc != c_prev)  \n                    if g_new > target: continue  \n                    ndp[cc, g_new] = min(ndp.get((cc, g_new), float('inf')), dp[c_prev, g_prev] + (cost[i][cc-1] if c == 0 else 0))  \n            dp, ndp = ndp, {}  \n          \n        return min([dp[c, g] for c, g in dp if g == target] or [-1])  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Three-dimension/README.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Three-dimension/README.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Three dimension","title":"Three dimension Overview","displayTitle":"Three dimension Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/10._Regular_Expression_Matching.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/10._Regular_Expression_Matching.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"10. Regular Expression Matching.md","displayTitle":"10. Regular Expression Matching","problemNumber":10,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/regular-expression-matching/discuss/665501/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"10. Regular Expression Matching.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/regular-expression-matching/discuss/665501/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down](https://leetcode.com/problems/regular-expression-matching/discuss/665501/Python-Concise-DP-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down)\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/1130._Minimum_Cost_Tree_From_Leaf_Values.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/1130._Minimum_Cost_Tree_From_Leaf_Values.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"1130. Minimum Cost Tree From Leaf Values.md","displayTitle":"1130. Minimum Cost Tree From Leaf Values","problemNumber":1130,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-cost-tree-from-leaf-values/discuss/667294/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"1130. Minimum Cost Tree From Leaf Values.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-cost-tree-from-leaf-values/discuss/667294/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/1140._Stone_Game_II.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/1140._Stone_Game_II.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"1140. Stone Game II.md","displayTitle":"1140. Stone Game II","problemNumber":1140,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/stone-game-ii/discuss/345230/Python-DP-Solution"],"markdown":"1140. Stone Game II.md\n\tcontest/competitive games  \n\t\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/stone-game-ii/discuss/345230/Python-DP-Solution\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/115._Distinct_Subsequences.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/115._Distinct_Subsequences.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"115. Distinct Subsequences.md","displayTitle":"115. Distinct Subsequences","problemNumber":115,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/distinct-subsequences/discuss/673798/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"115. Distinct Subsequences.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/distinct-subsequences/discuss/673798/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/1548._The_Most_Similar_Path_in_a_Graph.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/1548._The_Most_Similar_Path_in_a_Graph.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"1548. The Most Similar Path in a Graph.md","displayTitle":"1548. The Most Similar Path in a Graph","problemNumber":1548,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1548. The Most Similar Path in a Graph.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def mostSimilar(self, n: int, roads: List[List[int]], names: List[str], targetPath: List[str]) -> List[int]:  \n        graph, succ = defaultdict(set), {}  \n        for u, v in roads:  \n            graph[u].add(v)  \n            graph[v].add(u)  \n          \n        for i in range(n):  \n            graph[-1].add(i)  \n          \n        @lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(idx, city_idx):  \n            if idx >= len(targetPath):  \n                return 0  \n              \n            edit = math.inf  \n            for nxt in graph[city_idx]:  \n                n_edit = dp(idx+1, nxt) + (not (targetPath[idx] == names[nxt]))  \n                if n_edit < edit:  \n                    edit = n_edit  \n                    succ[(idx, city_idx)] = nxt  \n            return edit  \n          \n        dp(0, -1)  \n\n        ret = [-1]  \n        while len(ret) <= len(targetPath):  \n            ret.append(succ[(len(ret)-1, ret[-1])])  \n              \n        return ret[1:]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/188._Best_Time_to_Buy_and_Sell_Stock_IV.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/188._Best_Time_to_Buy_and_Sell_Stock_IV.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"188. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock IV.md","displayTitle":"188. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock IV","problemNumber":188,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iv/discuss/676357/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"188. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock IV.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iv/discuss/676357/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/221._Maximal_Square.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/221._Maximal_Square.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"221. Maximal Square.md","displayTitle":"221. Maximal Square","problemNumber":221,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"221. Maximal Square.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maximalSquare(self, M: List[List[str]]) -> int:  \n        if not M or not M[0]: return 0  \n        m, n = len(M), len(M[0])  \n        h, max_l = [0] * n, 0  \n        '''  \n        # bottom up: Time O(M*N) Space O(M*N)  \n        dp = [[0]*(n+1) for _ in range(m+1)]  \n          \n        for i in range(m):  \n            w = 0  \n            for j in range(n):  \n                if M[i][j] == '0':  \n                    w, h[j], dp[i+1][j+1] = 0, 0, 0  \n                else:  \n                    w, h[j] = w+1, h[j]+1  \n                    dp[i+1][j+1] = min(w, h[j], dp[i][j]+1)  \n                    max_l = max(max_l, dp[i+1][j+1])  \n        return max_l * max_l  \n        '''  \n        # bottom up: Time O(M*N) Space O(N)  \n        dp, ndp = [0] * (n+1), [0] * (n+1)  \n        for i in range(m):  \n            w = 0  \n            for j in range(n):  \n                if M[i][j] == '0':  \n                    w, h[j], ndp[j+1] = 0, 0, 0  \n                else:  \n                    w, h[j] = w+1, h[j]+1  \n                    ndp[j+1] = min(w, h[j], dp[j]+1)  \n                    max_l = max(max_l, ndp[j+1])  \n            dp, ndp = ndp, [0] * (n+1)  \n        return max_l * max_l  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/312._Burst_Balloons.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/312._Burst_Balloons.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"312. Burst Balloons.md","displayTitle":"312. Burst Balloons","problemNumber":312,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/burst-balloons/discuss/665527/Python-Concise-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"312. Burst Balloons.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/burst-balloons/discuss/665527/Python-Concise-Botton-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/375._Guess_Number_Higher_or_Lower_II.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/375._Guess_Number_Higher_or_Lower_II.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"375. Guess Number Higher or Lower II.md","displayTitle":"375. Guess Number Higher or Lower II","problemNumber":375,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"375. Guess Number Higher or Lower II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def getMoneyAmount(self, n: int) -> int:  \n        @lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(l, r):  \n            if r-l <= 1:  \n                return 0  \n              \n            ret = math.inf  \n            for i in range(l, r):  \n                ret = min(ret, i + max(dp(l, i), dp(i+1, r)))  \n            return ret  \n          \n        return dp(1, n+1)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/410._Split_Array_Largest_Sum.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/410._Split_Array_Largest_Sum.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"410. Split Array Largest Sum.md","displayTitle":"410. Split Array Largest Sum","problemNumber":410,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/split-array-largest-sum/discuss/676272/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"410. Split Array Largest Sum.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/split-array-largest-sum/discuss/676272/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/44._Wildcard_Matching.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/44._Wildcard_Matching.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"44. Wildcard Matching.md","displayTitle":"44. Wildcard Matching","problemNumber":44,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/wildcard-matching/discuss/687707/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"44. Wildcard Matching.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/wildcard-matching/discuss/687707/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/5._Longest_Palindromic_Substring.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/5._Longest_Palindromic_Substring.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"5. Longest Palindromic Substring.md","displayTitle":"5. Longest Palindromic Substring","problemNumber":5,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-substring/discuss/663984/python-concise-dp-on2"],"markdown":"5. Longest Palindromic Substring.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-substring/discuss/663984/python-concise-dp-on2](https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-substring/discuss/663984/python-concise-dp-on2)\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/562._Longest_Line_of_Consecutive_One_in_Matrix.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/562._Longest_Line_of_Consecutive_One_in_Matrix.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"562. Longest Line of Consecutive One in Matrix.md","displayTitle":"562. Longest Line of Consecutive One in Matrix","problemNumber":562,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"562. Longest Line of Consecutive One in Matrix.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def longestLine(self, M: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        if not M: return 0  \n        m, n = len(M) , len(M[0])  \n          \n        '''  \n        @lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(r, c):  \n            if not (0 <= r < m and 0 <= c < n) or M[r][c] != 1:  \n                return (0, 0, 0, 0)  \n            # left, left-top, top  \n            left, lt, top, rt = dp(r, c-1)[0]+1, dp(r-1, c-1)[1]+1, dp(r-1, c)[2]+1, dp(r-1, c+1)[3]+1  \n            return (left, lt, top, rt)  \n          \n        return max(max(dp(r, c)) for r in range(m) for c in range(n))  \n        '''  \n        dp, ret = Counter(), 0  \n          \n        for i, row in enumerate(M):  \n            for j, val in enumerate(row):  \n                dp[(i, 0)] = dp[(i, 0)] + 1 if val else 0  \n                dp[(j, 1)] = dp[(j, 1)] + 1 if val else 0  \n                dp[(i+j, 2)] = dp[(i+j, 2)] + 1 if val else 0  \n                dp[(j-i, 3)] = dp[(j-i, 3)] + 1 if val else 0  \n                  \n                ret = max((ret, dp[(i, 0)], dp[(j, 1)], dp[(i+j, 2)], dp[(j-i, 3)]))  \n\n        return ret        \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/72._Edit_Distance.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/72._Edit_Distance.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"72. Edit Distance.md","displayTitle":"72. Edit Distance","problemNumber":72,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/edit-distance/discuss/663855/Python-Concise-memorization-%2B-Botton-up"],"markdown":"72. Edit Distance.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/edit-distance/discuss/663855/Python-Concise-memorization-%2B-Botton-up](https://leetcode.com/problems/edit-distance/discuss/663855/Python-Concise-memorization-%2B-Botton-up)\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/727._Minimum_Window_Subsequence.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/727._Minimum_Window_Subsequence.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"727. Minimum Window Subsequence.md","displayTitle":"727. Minimum Window Subsequence","problemNumber":727,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"727. Minimum Window Subsequence.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minWindow(self, S: str, T: str) -> str:  \n        @lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(x, y):  \n            if y == len(T): return x  \n            if x >= len(S): return math.inf  \n              \n            if S[x] != T[y]:  \n                return dp(x+1, y)  \n            else:                  \n                return dp(x+1, y+1)  \n        ret = None  \n        for i in range(len(S)):  \n            k = dp(i, 0)  \n            if k != math.inf and (not ret or len(ret) > (k-i)):  \n                ret = S[i:k]  \n        return ret if ret else ''  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/730._Count_Different_Palindromic_Subsequences.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/730._Count_Different_Palindromic_Subsequences.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"730. Count Different Palindromic Subsequences.md","displayTitle":"730. Count Different Palindromic Subsequences","problemNumber":730,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"730. Count Different Palindromic Subsequences.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def countPalindromicSubsequences(self, S):  \n        import functools  \n        @functools.lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(start, end):     #returns the number of distinct palindromes in S[start:end]  \n            count = 0  \n            segment = S[start:end]  \n            for x in 'abcd':  \n                try:  \n                    i = segment.index(x) + start  # the starting index in S  \n                    j = segment.rindex(x) + start # the ending index in S  \n                except:  \n                    continue  \n                count += dp(i+1, j) + 2 if i != j else 1  \n            return count % 1000000007  \n        return dp(0, len(S))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/87._Scramble_String.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/87._Scramble_String.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"87. Scramble String.md","displayTitle":"87. Scramble String","problemNumber":87,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"87. Scramble String.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isScramble(self, s1: str, s2: str) -> bool:  \n        # Top down: Time O(N^3) Space O(N^3)  \n        import functools  \n        @functools.lru_cache(None)  \n        def dp(s1, s2, rev):  \n            if s1 == s2 or s1 == s2[::-1]: return True  \n            return any(dp(s1[:i], s2[:i], True) and dp(s1[i:], s2[i:], True) for i in range(1, len(s1))) or \\  \n                   (rev and dp(s1, s2[::-1], not rev))  \n        return dp(s1, s2, True)        \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/95._Unique_Binary_Search_Trees_II.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/95._Unique_Binary_Search_Trees_II.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"95. Unique Binary Search Trees II.md","displayTitle":"95. Unique Binary Search Trees II","problemNumber":95,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-binary-search-trees-ii/discuss/669241/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"95. Unique Binary Search Trees II.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-binary-search-trees-ii/discuss/669241/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down](https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-binary-search-trees-ii/discuss/669241/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down)\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/97._Interleaving_String.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/97._Interleaving_String.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"97. Interleaving String.md","displayTitle":"97. Interleaving String","problemNumber":97,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/interleaving-string/discuss/673764/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down"],"markdown":"97. Interleaving String.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/interleaving-string/discuss/673764/Python-Concise-DP-Bottom-up-%2B-Top-down\n\n"},{"id":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/README.md","path":"Dynamic-programming/Two-dimension/README.md","topic":"Dynamic programming","section":"Two dimension","title":"Two dimension Overview","displayTitle":"Two dimension Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Graph/1059._All_Paths_from_Source_Lead_to_Destination.md","path":"Graph/1059._All_Paths_from_Source_Lead_to_Destination.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Overview","title":"1059. All Paths from Source Lead to Destination.md","displayTitle":"1059. All Paths from Source Lead to Destination","problemNumber":1059,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"1059. All Paths from Source Lead to Destination.md\n"},{"id":"Graph/310._Minimum_Height_Trees.md","path":"Graph/310._Minimum_Height_Trees.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Overview","title":"310. Minimum Height Trees.md","displayTitle":"310. Minimum Height Trees","problemNumber":310,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"310. Minimum Height Trees.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findMinHeightTrees(self, n: int, edges: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:  \n        graph = defaultdict(set)  \n        for u, v in edges:  \n            graph[u].add(v)  \n            graph[v].add(u)  \n          \n        leaves = [i for i in range(n) if len(graph[i]) <= 1]  \n        while n > 2:  \n            n -= len(leaves)  \n            nl = []  \n            for u in leaves:  \n                for v in graph[u]:  \n                    graph[v].remove(u)  \n                    if len(graph[v]) == 1:  \n                        nl.append(v)  \n            leaves = nl  \n        return leaves  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/684._Redundant_Connection.md","path":"Graph/684._Redundant_Connection.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Overview","title":"684. Redundant Connection.md","displayTitle":"684. Redundant Connection","problemNumber":684,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"684. Redundant Connection.md\n\t## Key observation - What is a tree  \n\t1. Each node can has at most 1 parent. Root does not have a parent  \n\t2. No cycle  \n\t\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findRedundantConnection(self, edges: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:  \n        '''  \n        graph = defaultdict(dict)  \n        for i, (u, v) in enumerate(edges):  \n            graph[u][v] = i  \n            graph[v][u] = i  \n          \n        removed = set()  \n        q = [u for u in graph if len(graph[u]) == 1]  \n        while q:  \n            u = q.pop()  \n            v, idx = graph[u].popitem()  \n            removed.add(idx)  \n\n            del graph[v][u]  \n            if len(graph[v]) == 1:  \n                q.append(v)  \n          \n        return edges[max(i for i, edge in enumerate(edges) if i not in removed)]  \n        '''  \n        uf = {}  \n        def find(x):  \n            uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n            if x != uf[x]: uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n            return uf[x]  \n        def union(x, y):  \n            uf[find(x)] = uf[find(y)]  \n          \n        ret = None  \n        for u, v in edges:  \n            if find(u) == find(v):  \n                return [u, v]  \n            union(u, v)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/685._Redundant_Connection_II.md","path":"Graph/685._Redundant_Connection_II.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Overview","title":"685. Redundant Connection II.md","displayTitle":"685. Redundant Connection II","problemNumber":685,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"685. Redundant Connection II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findRedundantDirectedConnection(self, edges: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:  \n        def helper(edges, skip):  \n            uf = {}  \n            def find(x):  \n                uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n                if x != uf[x]: uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n                return uf[x]  \n            def union(x, y):  \n                uf[find(x)] = uf[find(y)]  \n\n            ret = None  \n            for idx, (u, v) in enumerate(edges):  \n                if idx == skip: continue  \n                if find(u) == find(v):  \n                    return [u, v]  \n                union(u, v)  \n            return []  \n        prev, cand = {}, []  \n        for i, (u, v) in enumerate(edges):  \n            if v in prev:  \n                cand = [prev[v], i]  \n                break  \n            prev[v] = i  \n              \n        if not cand: return helper(edges, -1)  \n        else:  \n            print(cand)  \n            if helper(edges, cand[1]):  \n                print(2)  \n                return edges[cand[0]]  \n            return edges[cand[1]]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Cycle-Detection/README.md","path":"Graph/Cycle-Detection/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Cycle Detection","title":"https://yonglife.com/2020/08/22/Detect-Cycle-in-a-Graph/","displayTitle":"Cycle Detection Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://yonglife.com/2020/08/22/Detect-Cycle-in-a-Graph/"],"markdown":"README.md\nhttps://yonglife.com/2020/08/22/Detect-Cycle-in-a-Graph/\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Dijkstra_Bellman-Ford/1514._Path_with_Maximum_Probability.md","path":"Graph/Dijkstra_Bellman-Ford/1514._Path_with_Maximum_Probability.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Dijkstra Bellman Ford","title":"1514. Path with Maximum Probability.md","displayTitle":"1514. Path with Maximum Probability","problemNumber":1514,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1514. Path with Maximum Probability.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maxProbability(self, n: int, edges: List[List[int]], succProb: List[float], start: int, end: int) -> float:  \n        '''  \n        # Bellman-Ford: Time O(V*E)  \n        dist = defaultdict(int)  \n        dist[start] = 1  \n        for i in range(n):  \n            cnt = 0  \n            for (u, v), w in zip(edges, succProb):  \n                if dist[v] < dist[u] * w:  \n                    dist[v] = dist[u] * w  \n                    cnt += 1  \n                if dist[u] < dist[v] * w:  \n                    dist[u] = dist[v] * w  \n                    cnt += 1  \n            if cnt == 0:  \n                break  \n        return dist[end]  \n        '''  \n        # Dijkstra  \n        graph = defaultdict(dict)  \n        for (u, v), w in zip(edges, succProb):  \n            graph[u][v] = w  \n            graph[v][u] = w  \n        dist = defaultdict(int)  \n        dist[start] = 1  \n        q = [(-1, start)]  \n        while q:  \n            _, u = heapq.heappop(q)  \n            if u == end: return dist[u]              \n            for v, w in graph[u].items():  \n                if dist[v] < dist[u] * w:  \n                    dist[v] = dist[u] * w  \n                    heapq.heappush(q, (-dist[v], v))  \n        return dist[end]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Dijkstra_Bellman-Ford/743._Network_Delay_Time.md","path":"Graph/Dijkstra_Bellman-Ford/743._Network_Delay_Time.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Dijkstra Bellman Ford","title":"743. Network Delay Time.md","displayTitle":"743. Network Delay Time","problemNumber":743,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"743. Network Delay Time.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def networkDelayTime(self, times: List[List[int]], N: int, K: int) -> int:  \n        graph = defaultdict(dict)  \n        for u, v, w in times:  \n            graph[u][v] = w  \n        '''[]  \n        # Dijkstra  \n        heap, dist = [(0, K)], defaultdict(lambda: math.inf)  \n        dist[K] = 0  \n        while heap:  \n            _, u = heapq.heappop(heap)  \n              \n            for v, w in graph[u].items():  \n                if dist[v] > dist[u] + w:  \n                    dist[v] = dist[u] + w  \n                    heapq.heappush(heap, (dist[v], v))  \n                  \n        return max(dist.values()) if all(dist[v] != math.inf for v in range(1, N+1)) else -1  \n        '''  \n        # Bellman ford  \n        dist = defaultdict(lambda: math.inf)  \n        dist[K] = 0  \n        for i in range(N):  \n            cnt = 0  \n            for u, v, w in times:  \n                if dist[v] > dist[u] + w:  \n                    dist[v] = dist[u] + w  \n                    cnt += 1  \n            if cnt == 0: break  \n        return max(dist.values()) if all(dist[v] != math.inf for v in range(1, N+1)) else -1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Dijkstra_Bellman-Ford/README.md","path":"Graph/Dijkstra_Bellman-Ford/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Dijkstra Bellman Ford","title":"[Graph-Dijkstra](https://yonglife.com/2019/06/01/Graph-Dijkstra/)","displayTitle":"Dijkstra Bellman Ford Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://yonglife.com/2019/06/01/Graph-Bellman-Ford/","https://yonglife.com/2019/06/01/Graph-Dijkstra/"],"markdown":"README.md\n[Graph-Dijkstra](https://yonglife.com/2019/06/01/Graph-Dijkstra/)\n[Bellman-Ford](https://yonglife.com/2019/06/01/Graph-Bellman-Ford/)\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Euler-path/332._Reconstruct_Itinerary.md","path":"Graph/Euler-path/332._Reconstruct_Itinerary.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Euler path","title":"332. Reconstruct Itinerary.md","displayTitle":"332. Reconstruct Itinerary","problemNumber":332,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"332. Reconstruct Itinerary.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findItinerary(self, tickets: List[List[str]]) -> List[str]:  \n        graph = defaultdict(list)  \n        for a, b in sorted(tickets)[::-1]:  \n            graph[a].append(b)  \n          \n        ret = []  \n        def dfs(cur):  \n            while graph[cur]:  \n                nxt = graph[cur].pop()  \n                dfs(nxt)  \n            ret.append(cur)  \n        dfs('JFK')  \n        return ret[::-1]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Euler-path/README.md","path":"Graph/Euler-path/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Euler path","title":"class Solution:","displayTitle":"Euler path Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n```python\nclass Solution:  \n    def EulerPath(self, tickets: List[List[str]]) -> List[str]:  \n        graph = defaultdict(list)  \n        for a, b in ticket:  \n            graph[a].append(b)  \n          \n        ret = []  \n        def dfs(cur):  \n            while graph[cur]:  \n                nxt = graph[cur].pop()  \n                dfs(nxt)  \n            ret.append(cur)  \n        dfs('JFK')  \n        return ret[::-1]\n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Floyd–Warshall/399._Evaluate_Division.md","path":"Graph/Floyd–Warshall/399._Evaluate_Division.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Floyd–Warshall","title":"399. Evaluate Division.md","displayTitle":"399. Evaluate Division","problemNumber":399,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"399. Evaluate Division.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def calcEquation(self, equations: List[List[str]], values: List[float], queries: List[List[str]]) -> List[float]:  \n        graph = defaultdict(dict)  \n        for (u, v), w in zip(equations, values):  \n            graph[u][v] = w  \n            graph[v][u] = 1 / w  \n          \n        for k in graph:  \n            for i in graph:  \n                for j in graph:  \n                    if k in graph[i] and j in graph[k]:  \n                        graph[i][j] = graph[i][k] * graph[k][j]  \n          \n        return [(graph[u][v] if v in graph[u] else -1) for u, v in queries]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Floyd–Warshall/README.md","path":"Graph/Floyd–Warshall/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Floyd–Warshall","title":"Floyd–Warshall Overview","displayTitle":"Floyd–Warshall Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Graph/Minimal-Spinning-Tree/README.md","path":"Graph/Minimal-Spinning-Tree/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Minimal Spinning Tree","title":"https://yonglife.com/2017/04/24/Minimum-spanning-tree/","displayTitle":"Minimal Spinning Tree Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://yonglife.com/2017/04/24/Minimum-spanning-tree/"],"markdown":"README.md\nhttps://yonglife.com/2017/04/24/Minimum-spanning-tree/\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/README.md","path":"Graph/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Overview","title":"Overview","displayTitle":"Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Tarjan's-algorithm/1192._Critical_Connections_in_a_Network.md","path":"Graph/Tarjan's-algorithm/1192._Critical_Connections_in_a_Network.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Tarjan's algorithm","title":"1192. Critical Connections in a Network.md","displayTitle":"1192. Critical Connections in a Network","problemNumber":1192,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1192. Critical Connections in a Network.md\n\t## Find cut edge  \n\t\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def criticalConnections(self, n: int, edges: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int]]:  \n        graph = [[] for i in range(n)]  \n        for u, v in edges:  \n            graph[u].append(v)  \n            graph[v].append(u)  \n          \n        ids, low = [-1] * n, [0] * n  \n        id_max, bridges = 0, []  \n          \n        def dfs(u, parent, bridges):  \n            nonlocal id_max  \n            id_max += 1  \n            ids[u] = low[u] = id_max  \n              \n            for v in graph[u]:  \n                if v == parent: continue  \n                if ids[v] == -1:  \n                    dfs(v, u, bridges)  \n                    low[u] = min(low[u], low[v])   \n                    if ids[u] < low[v]:  \n                        bridges.append([u, v])  \n                else:  \n                    low[u] = min(low[u], ids[v])  \n        dfs(u, -1, bridges)  \n        return bridges  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Tarjan's-algorithm/README.md","path":"Graph/Tarjan's-algorithm/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Tarjan's algorithm","title":"Tarjan's algorithm Overview","displayTitle":"Tarjan's algorithm Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Graph/Topologic-sort/1048._Longest_String_Chain.md","path":"Graph/Topologic-sort/1048._Longest_String_Chain.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Topologic sort","title":"1048. Longest String Chain.md","displayTitle":"1048. Longest String Chain","problemNumber":1048,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1048. Longest String Chain.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def longestStrChain(self, words: List[str]) -> int:  \n        words_set = set(words)  \n        prev, next = defaultdict(set), defaultdict(set)  \n        for word in words:  \n            for i in range(len(word)+1):  \n                for c in string.ascii_lowercase:  \n                    nw = word[:i] + c + word[i:]  \n                    if nw in words_set:  \n                        next[word].add(nw)  \n                        prev[nw].add(word)  \n        ret = 0  \n        pq = [(1, word) for word in words if len(next[word]) == 0]  \n        dist = defaultdict(int)  \n        while pq:  \n            size, word = pq.pop()  \n            ret = max(ret, size)  \n            for pw in prev[word]:  \n                next[pw].remove(word)  \n                dist[pw] = max(dist[pw], size+1)  \n                if len(next[pw]) == 0:  \n                    pq.append((max(dist[pw], size+1), pw))  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Topologic-sort/1203._Sort_Items_by_Groups_Respecting_Dependencies.md","path":"Graph/Topologic-sort/1203._Sort_Items_by_Groups_Respecting_Dependencies.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Topologic sort","title":"1203. Sort Items by Groups Respecting Dependencies.md","displayTitle":"1203. Sort Items by Groups Respecting Dependencies","problemNumber":1203,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1203. Sort Items by Groups Respecting Dependencies.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def sortItems(self, n: int, m: int, group: List[int], beforeItems: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:  \n        def topo_sort(vertexs, succ, pre):  \n            q = [v for v in vertexs if len(pre[v]) == 0]  \n            ret = []  \n            while q:  \n                u = q.pop()  \n                ret.append(u)          \n                for v in succ[u]:  \n                    pre[v].remove(u)  \n                    if not pre[v]:  \n                        q.append(v)  \n            if len(ret) != len(vertexs):  \n                return []  \n            return ret  \n        v2g, g2v = {}, defaultdict(set)  \n        for u, g in enumerate(group):  \n            if g == -1:  \n                g = m  \n                m += 1  \n            v2g[u] = g  \n            g2v[g].add(u)  \n          \n        i_succ, i_pre = defaultdict(set), defaultdict(set)  \n        g_succ, g_pre = defaultdict(set), defaultdict(set)  \n        for v, nxt in enumerate(beforeItems):  \n            for u in nxt:  \n                if v2g[v] == v2g[u]:  \n                    i_succ[u].add(v)  \n                    i_pre[v].add(u)  \n                else:  \n                    g_succ[v2g[u]].add(v2g[v])  \n                    g_pre[v2g[v]].add(v2g[u])  \n          \n        group_order = topo_sort(set(v2g.values()), g_succ, g_pre)  \n        print(group_order)  \n        if not group_order: return []  \n          \n        ret = []  \n        for g in group_order:  \n            items_order = topo_sort(g2v[g], i_succ, i_pre)  \n            if len(items_order) != len(g2v[g]):  \n                return []  \n            ret += items_order  \n        return ret   \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Topologic-sort/207._Course_Schedule.md","path":"Graph/Topologic-sort/207._Course_Schedule.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Topologic sort","title":"207. Course Schedule.md","displayTitle":"207. Course Schedule","problemNumber":207,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"207. Course Schedule.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def canFinish(self, numCourses: int, P: List[List[int]]) -> bool:  \n        graph = defaultdict(list)  \n        indegree = Counter()  \n        for a, b in P:  \n            graph[b].append(a)  \n            indegree[a] += 1  \n        ret, q = [], [i for i in range(numCourses) if indegree[i] == 0]  \n        # BFS  \n        while q:  \n            ret.append(q.pop())  \n            for nxt in graph[ret[-1]]:  \n                indegree[nxt] -= 1  \n                if indegree[nxt] == 0:  \n                    q.append(nxt)  \n        return len(ret) == numCourses  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Topologic-sort/210._Course_Schedule_II.md","path":"Graph/Topologic-sort/210._Course_Schedule_II.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Topologic sort","title":"210. Course Schedule II.md","displayTitle":"210. Course Schedule II","problemNumber":210,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"210. Course Schedule II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findOrder(self, N: int, P: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:  \n        graph = defaultdict(list)  \n        degree = Counter()  \n        for a, b in P:  \n            degree[a] += 1  \n            graph[b].append(a)  \n        q = deque([i for i in range(N) if degree[i] == 0])  \n        ret = []  \n        while q:  \n            c = q.popleft()  \n            ret.append(c)  \n            for nxt in graph[c]:  \n                degree[nxt] -= 1  \n                if degree[nxt] == 0:  \n                    q.append(nxt)  \n        return ret if len(ret) == N else []  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Topologic-sort/329._Longest_Increasing_Path_in_a_Matrix.md","path":"Graph/Topologic-sort/329._Longest_Increasing_Path_in_a_Matrix.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Topologic sort","title":"329. Longest Increasing Path in a Matrix.md","displayTitle":"329. Longest Increasing Path in a Matrix","problemNumber":329,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"329. Longest Increasing Path in a Matrix.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def longestIncreasingPath(self, M: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        prev, next = defaultdict(set), defaultdict(set)  \n        if not M or not M[0]: return 0  \n        m, n = len(M), len(M[0])  \n        for i in range(m):  \n            for j in range(n):  \n                for x, y in [(-1, 0), (1, 0), (0, -1), (0, 1)]:  \n                    r, c = i+x, j+y  \n                    if not (0 <= r < m and 0 <= c < n): continue  \n                    if M[i][j] < M[r][c]:  \n                        next[(i, j)].add((r, c))  \n                        prev[(r, c)].add((i, j))  \n        pq = [(point, 1) for point in prev if len(next[point]) == 0]  \n        if not pq: return 1  \n        dist = defaultdict(lambda: 1)  \n        for (point, size) in pq:              \n            for pre in prev[point]:  \n                dist[pre] = max(dist[pre], size+1)  \n                next[pre].remove(point)  \n                if len(next[pre]) == 0:  \n                    pq.append((pre, dist[pre]))  \n\n        return max(dist.values())  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Topologic-sort/802._Find_Eventual_Safe_States.md","path":"Graph/Topologic-sort/802._Find_Eventual_Safe_States.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Topologic sort","title":"802. Find Eventual Safe States.md","displayTitle":"802. Find Eventual Safe States","problemNumber":802,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"802. Find Eventual Safe States.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def eventualSafeNodes(self, POINTS: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:  \n        graph = defaultdict(set)  \n        degree = Counter()  \n        for u, nxt in enumerate(POINTS):  \n            for v in nxt:  \n                graph[v].add(u)  \n            degree[u] = len(nxt)  \n          \n        q = [i for i in range(len(POINTS)) if degree[i] == 0]  \n        ret = []  \n        while q:  \n            u = q.pop()  \n            ret.append(u)  \n            for v in graph[u]:  \n                degree[v] -= 1  \n                if degree[v] == 0:  \n                    q.append(v)  \n        return sorted(ret)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Graph/Topologic-sort/README.md","path":"Graph/Topologic-sort/README.md","topic":"Graph","section":"Topologic sort","title":"def topo_sort(n: int, edges: List[List[int]]):","displayTitle":"Topologic sort Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n```python  \ndef topo_sort(n: int, edges: List[List[int]]):  \n    '''  \n    Args:  \n      n: graph contains vertex 0, 1, 2, ..... n-1  \n      edges: [[u, v], [u, v], ....]  \n    '''  \n    succ, pred = defaultdict(set), defaultdict(set)  \n    for u, v in edges:  \n        succ[u].add(v)  \n        pred[v].add(u)  \n    ret, q = [], [u for u in range(n) if len(pred[u]) == 0]  \n    while q:  \n        u = q.pop()  \n        ret.append(u)  \n\n        for v in succ[u]:  \n            pred[v].remove(u)  \n            if not pred[v]:  \n                q.append(v)  \n      \n    if len(ret) != n+1:  \n        return []  \n    return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/1060._Missing_Element_in_Sorted_Array.md","path":"List/Binary-search/1060._Missing_Element_in_Sorted_Array.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"1060. Missing Element in Sorted Array.md","displayTitle":"1060. Missing Element in Sorted Array","problemNumber":1060,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1060. Missing Element in Sorted Array.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def missingElement(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:  \n        '''  \n        prev = nums[0]-1  \n        for val in nums:  \n            if k <= val - prev - 1:  \n                return prev + k  \n            else:  \n                k -= val - prev - 1  \n                prev = val  \n        return prev + k  \n        '''  \n        def count_space(idx):  \n            return nums[idx] - nums[0] - 1 - (idx - 1) # 2 4 7  \n          \n        l, r = 0, len(nums)-1  \n        while l < r:  \n            mid = (l+r) // 2  \n            space = count_space(mid)  \n            if space >= k:  \n                r = mid  \n            else:  \n                l = mid + 1  \n        if count_space(l) >= k:  \n            l -= 1  \n        return nums[l] + k - count_space(l)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/1146._Snapshot_Array.md","path":"List/Binary-search/1146._Snapshot_Array.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"1146. Snapshot Array.md","displayTitle":"1146. Snapshot Array","problemNumber":1146,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1146. Snapshot Array.md\n```python  \nclass SnapshotArray:  \n\n    def __init__(self, length: int):  \n        self.d = defaultdict(list)  \n        for i in range(length):  \n            self.d[i].append((0, 0))  \n        self.v = 0  \n\n    def set(self, index: int, val: int) -> None:  \n        self.d[index].append((self.v, val))  \n\n    def snap(self) -> int:  \n        self.v += 1  \n        return self.v - 1  \n\n    def get(self, index: int, snap_id: int) -> int:  \n        idx = bisect.bisect(self.d[index], (snap_id, float'inf')) - 1  \n        return self.d[index][idx][1]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/1231._Divide_Chocolate.md","path":"List/Binary-search/1231._Divide_Chocolate.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"1231. Divide Chocolate.md","displayTitle":"1231. Divide Chocolate","problemNumber":1231,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1231. Divide Chocolate.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maximizeSweetness(self, sweetness: List[int], K: int) -> int:  \n        def can(size):  \n            cnt, cur = 0, 0  \n            for val in sweetness:  \n                cur += val  \n                if cur >= size:  \n                    cnt += 1  \n                    cur = 0  \n            return cnt >= K+1  \n          \n        l, r = 0, sum(sweetness)  \n        while l < r:  \n            mid = (l+r) // 2  \n            if can(mid):  \n                l = mid + 1  \n            else:  \n                r = mid  \n        return l if can(l) else l-1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/240._Search_a_2D_Matrix_II.md","path":"List/Binary-search/240._Search_a_2D_Matrix_II.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"240. Search a 2D Matrix II.md","displayTitle":"240. Search a 2D Matrix II","problemNumber":240,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"240. Search a 2D Matrix II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def searchMatrix(self, matrix, target):  \n        \"\"\"  \n        :type matrix: List[List[int]]  \n        :type target: int  \n        :rtype: bool  \n        \"\"\"  \n        if not matrix or not matrix[0]: return False  \n        m, n = len(matrix), len(matrix[0])  \n        x, y = 0, n-1  \n        while 0 <= x < m and 0 <= y < n:  \n            if matrix[x][y] == target:  \n                return True  \n            if matrix[x][y] < target:  \n                x += 1  \n            else:  \n                y -= 1  \n        return False  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/327._Count_of_Range_Sum.md","path":"List/Binary-search/327._Count_of_Range_Sum.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"327. Count of Range Sum.md","displayTitle":"327. Count of Range Sum","problemNumber":327,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"327. Count of Range Sum.md\n```python  \nfrom sortedcontainers import SortedList  \nclass Solution:  \n    def countRangeSum(self, nums: List[int], lower: int, upper: int) -> int:  \n        pre_sum, sums = 0, SortedList([0])  \n        ret = 0  \n        for num in nums:  \n            pre_sum += num  \n            # print(sums)  \n            # lower <= pre_sum - x <= upper  \n            # pre_sum - lower >= x >= pre_sum - upper  \n            ret += sums.bisect_right(pre_sum - lower) - sums.bisect_left(pre_sum - upper)  \n            sums.add(pre_sum)  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/4._Median_of_Two_Sorted_Arrays.md","path":"List/Binary-search/4._Median_of_Two_Sorted_Arrays.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"4. Median of Two Sorted Arrays.md","displayTitle":"4. Median of Two Sorted Arrays","problemNumber":4,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"4. Median of Two Sorted Arrays.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findMedianSortedArrays(self, nums1: List[int], nums2: List[int]) -> float:  \n        if len(nums1) > len(nums2):  \n            nums1, nums2 = nums2, nums1  \n              \n        m, n = len(nums1), len(nums2)  \n        l, r, half = 0, m, (m+n) // 2  \n          \n        while l <= r:  \n            mid = (l+r) // 2  \n            l1, r1 = nums1[mid-1] if mid-1>=0 else -math.inf, nums1[mid] if mid<m else math.inf  \n            size_2 = half-mid  \n            l2, r2 = nums2[size_2-1] if size_2-1 >= 0 else -math.inf, nums2[size_2] if size_2 < n else math.inf  \n              \n            if l1 > r2:  \n                r = mid  \n            elif l2 > r1:  \n                l = mid + 1  \n            else:  \n                if (m+n) % 2:  \n                    return min(r1, r2)  \n                else:  \n                    return (max(l1,l2) + min(r1,r2)) / 2  \n          \n        return 0  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/410._Split_Array_Largest_Sum.md","path":"List/Binary-search/410._Split_Array_Largest_Sum.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"410. Split Array Largest Sum.md","displayTitle":"410. Split Array Largest Sum","problemNumber":410,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"410. Split Array Largest Sum.md\n\tGuess answer by using binary search  \n\t\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def splitArray(self, nums: List[int], m: int) -> int:  \n        def valid_sum(max_sum):  \n            cnt, cur = 1, 0  \n            for num in nums:  \n                cur += num  \n                if cur > max_sum:  \n                    cnt += 1  \n                    cur = num  \n                    if cnt > m:  \n                        return False  \n            return True  \n        # Binary search  \n        l, r = max(nums), sum(nums)  \n        while l < r:  \n            mid = (l+r) // 2  \n            if valid_sum(mid):  \n                r = mid  \n            else:  \n                l = mid+1  \n        return l  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/5455._Minimum_Number_of_Days_to_Make_m_Bouquets.md","path":"List/Binary-search/5455._Minimum_Number_of_Days_to_Make_m_Bouquets.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"5455. Minimum Number of Days to Make m Bouquets.md","displayTitle":"5455. Minimum Number of Days to Make m Bouquets","problemNumber":5455,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"5455. Minimum Number of Days to Make m Bouquets.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minDays(self, B: List[int], m: int, k: int) -> int:  \n        def ok(day):  \n            fl = 0  \n            cnt = 0  \n            for d in B:  \n                fl = fl + 1 if day >= d else 0  \n                if fl >= k:  \n                    cnt += 1  \n                    fl = 0  \n            return cnt >= m  \n\n        l, r = min(B), max(B)+1  \n        while l < r:  \n            #print(f'{l} {r}')  \n            mid = (l+r) // 2  \n            if ok(mid):  \n                r = mid  \n            else:  \n                l = mid + 1  \n        return l if l <= max(B) else -1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/635._Design_Log_Storage_System.md","path":"List/Binary-search/635._Design_Log_Storage_System.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"635. Design Log Storage System.md","displayTitle":"635. Design Log Storage System","problemNumber":635,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"635. Design Log Storage System.md\n```python  \nclass LogSystem:  \n\n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.data = []  \n\n    def put(self, id: int, timestamp: str) -> None:  \n        bisect.insort_left(self.data, (timestamp, id))  \n\n    def retrieve(self, s: str, e: str, gra: str) -> List[int]:  \n        gra_to_idx = {  \n            'Year': 4,  \n            'Month': 7,  \n            'Day': 10,  \n            'Hour': 13,  \n            'Minute': 16,  \n            'Second': 19  \n        }  \n        s = s[:gra_to_idx[gra]]  \n        e = e[:gra_to_idx[gra]]+':'+'9'*32  \n\n        idx1, idx2 = bisect.bisect_left(self.data, (s, -math.inf)), bisect.bisect(self.data, (e, math.inf))  \n        return [item[1] for item in self.data[idx1:idx2]]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Binary-search/README.md","path":"List/Binary-search/README.md","topic":"List","section":"Binary search","title":"> Ideal","displayTitle":"Binary search Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n> Ideal  \n\n1. Binary search can be used to guess answer in a known range.  \n\nLeverage library if it is available.  \n - Python: `bisect.bisect_left`, `bisect.bisect_right`  \n - C++: `lower_bound`, `upper_bound`\n\n"},{"id":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/1383._Maximum_Performance_of_a_Team.md","path":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/1383._Maximum_Performance_of_a_Team.md","topic":"List","section":"Heap sort Priority Queue","title":"1383. Maximum Performance of a Team.md","displayTitle":"1383. Maximum Performance of a Team","problemNumber":1383,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1383. Maximum Performance of a Team.md\n```python  \nfrom sortedcontainers import SortedList  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maxPerformance(self, n: int, speed: List[int], efficiency: List[int], k: int) -> int:  \n        workers, MOD = SortedList(), 10 ** 9 + 7  \n          \n        ret = ss = 0  \n        for e, s in sorted(zip(efficiency, speed), reverse=True):  \n            workers.add(s)  \n            ss += s  \n              \n            if len(workers) > k:  \n                ss -= workers.pop(0)  \n              \n            ret = max(ret, e * ss)  \n          \n        return ret % MOD  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/215._Kth_Largest_Element_in_an_Array.md","path":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/215._Kth_Largest_Element_in_an_Array.md","topic":"List","section":"Heap sort Priority Queue","title":"215. Kth Largest Element in an Array.md","displayTitle":"215. Kth Largest Element in an Array","problemNumber":215,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"215. Kth Largest Element in an Array.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findKthLargest(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:  \n        pq = []  \n        for n in nums:  \n            heapq.heappush(pq, n)  \n            if len(pq) > k:  \n                heapq.heappop(pq)  \n        return heapq.heappop(pq)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/632._Smallest_Range_Covering_Elements_from_K_Lists.md","path":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/632._Smallest_Range_Covering_Elements_from_K_Lists.md","topic":"List","section":"Heap sort Priority Queue","title":"632. Smallest Range Covering Elements from K Lists.md","displayTitle":"632. Smallest Range Covering Elements from K Lists","problemNumber":632,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"632. Smallest Range Covering Elements from K Lists.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def smallestRange(self, nums: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:  \n        q = [(num[0], num, 1) for num in nums]  \n        heapq.heapify(q)  \n        rst = [min(q)[0], max(q)[0]]  \n        cur_max = max(q)[0]  \n        while True:  \n            val, num, idx = heapq.heappop(q)  \n            if idx == len(num):  \n                return rst  \n            heapq.heappush(q, (num[idx], num, idx+1))  \n            cur_max = max(num[idx], cur_max)  \n            if cur_max - q[0][0] < rst[1] - rst[0]:  \n                rst = [q[0][0], cur_max]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/857._Minimum_Cost_to_Hire_K_Workers.md","path":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/857._Minimum_Cost_to_Hire_K_Workers.md","topic":"List","section":"Heap sort Priority Queue","title":"857. Minimum Cost to Hire K Workers.md","displayTitle":"857. Minimum Cost to Hire K Workers","problemNumber":857,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"857. Minimum Cost to Hire K Workers.md\n```python  \nfrom sortedcontainers import SortedList  \nclass Solution:  \n    def mincostToHireWorkers(self, quality: List[int], wage: List[int], K: int) -> float:  \n        ratios = [(w/q, (w, q)) for q, w in zip(quality, wage)]  \n        workers = SortedList()  \n        qualities, ret = 0, math.inf  \n          \n        for ratio, (w, q) in sorted(ratios):  \n            qualities += q  \n            workers.add(q)  \n              \n            if len(workers) > K:  \n                qualities -= workers.pop(-1)  \n              \n            if len(workers) == K:  \n                ret = min(ret, qualities * ratio)  \n          \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/973._K_Closest_Points_to_Origin.md","path":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/973._K_Closest_Points_to_Origin.md","topic":"List","section":"Heap sort Priority Queue","title":"973. K Closest Points to Origin.md","displayTitle":"973. K Closest Points to Origin","problemNumber":973,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"973. K Closest Points to Origin.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def kClosest(self, points: List[List[int]], K: int) -> List[List[int]]:  \n        pq = []  \n        for x, y in points:  \n            dis = (x*x + y*y)  \n            heapq.heappush(pq, (-dis, (x, y)))  \n            if len(pq) > K:  \n                heapq.heappop(pq)  \n        return [list(point) for _, point in pq]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/README.md","path":"List/Heap-sort-Priority-Queue/README.md","topic":"List","section":"Heap sort Priority Queue","title":"Heap sort Priority Queue Overview","displayTitle":"Heap sort Priority Queue Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"List/I-do-not-know..../443._String_Compression.md","path":"List/I-do-not-know..../443._String_Compression.md","topic":"List","section":"I do not know....","title":"443. String Compression.md","displayTitle":"443. String Compression","problemNumber":443,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"443. String Compression.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def repeatedSubstringPattern(self, s: str) -> bool:  \n        return s in (s*2)[1:-1]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/I-do-not-know..../686._Repeated_String_Match.md","path":"List/I-do-not-know..../686._Repeated_String_Match.md","topic":"List","section":"I do not know....","title":"686. Repeated String Match.md","displayTitle":"686. Repeated String Match","problemNumber":686,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"686. Repeated String Match.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def repeatedStringMatch(self, A: str, B: str) -> int:  \n        time = (len(B) // len(A)) + (1 if len(B) % len(A) else 0)  \n        if B in A * time: return time  \n        if B in A * (time+1): return time+1  \n        return -1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/I-do-not-know..../README.md","path":"List/I-do-not-know..../README.md","topic":"List","section":"I do not know....","title":"I do not know.... Overview","displayTitle":"I do not know.... Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"List/KMP/214._Shortest_Palindrome.md","path":"List/KMP/214._Shortest_Palindrome.md","topic":"List","section":"KMP","title":"214. Shortest Palindrome.md","displayTitle":"214. Shortest Palindrome","problemNumber":214,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"214. Shortest Palindrome.md\n\t214. Shortest Palindrome\n\n"},{"id":"List/KMP/README.md","path":"List/KMP/README.md","topic":"List","section":"KMP","title":"KMP Overview","displayTitle":"KMP Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"List/Math/899._Orderly_Queue.md","path":"List/Math/899._Orderly_Queue.md","topic":"List","section":"Math","title":"899. Orderly Queue.md","displayTitle":"899. Orderly Queue","problemNumber":899,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"899. Orderly Queue.md\n"},{"id":"List/Math/README.md","path":"List/Math/README.md","topic":"List","section":"Math","title":"I do not know.","displayTitle":"Math Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\nI do not know.   \nYou tell me how to solve it.\n\n"},{"id":"List/Palindromic/336._Palindrome_Pairs.md","path":"List/Palindromic/336._Palindrome_Pairs.md","topic":"List","section":"Palindromic","title":"336. Palindrome Pairs.md","displayTitle":"336. Palindrome Pairs","problemNumber":336,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"336. Palindrome Pairs.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def palindromePairs(self, words: List[str]) -> List[List[int]]:  \n        # N^2 * K  ->  N * K^2  \n        d = {word: i for i, word in enumerate(words)}  \n        ret = set()  \n        for i, word in enumerate(words):  \n            for j in range(0, len(word)+1):  \n                # i, k  \n                t = word[:j][::-1]  \n                if t in d and word+t == (word+t)[::-1] and d[t] != i:  \n                    ret.add((i, d[t]))  \n                # k, i  \n                t = word[len(word)-j:][::-1]  \n                if t in d and t+word == (t+word)[::-1] and d[t] != i:  \n                    ret.add((d[t], i))  \n        return list(ret)      \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Palindromic/5._Longest_Palindromic_Substring.md","path":"List/Palindromic/5._Longest_Palindromic_Substring.md","topic":"List","section":"Palindromic","title":"5. Longest Palindromic Substring.md","displayTitle":"5. Longest Palindromic Substring","problemNumber":5,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-substring/discuss/3337/Manacher-algorithm-in-Python-O(n"],"markdown":"5. Longest Palindromic Substring.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-substring/discuss/3337/Manacher-algorithm-in-Python-O(n)](https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindromic-substring/discuss/3337/Manacher-algorithm-in-Python-O(n))\n\t\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def longestPalindrome(self, s: str) -> str:  \n        ret, i = '', 0  \n          \n        while i < len(s):  \n            j = i  \n            while j < len(s) and s[j] == s[i]:  \n                j += 1  \n              \n            k = 0  \n            while i-k >= 0 and j+k-1 < len(s) and s[i-k] == s[j+k-1]:  \n                if j-i+2*k > len(ret):  \n                    ret = s[i-k:j+k]  \n                k += 1  \n              \n            i = j  \n        return ret            \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Palindromic/647._Palindromic_Substrings.md","path":"List/Palindromic/647._Palindromic_Substrings.md","topic":"List","section":"Palindromic","title":"647. Palindromic Substrings.md","displayTitle":"647. Palindromic Substrings","problemNumber":647,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"647. Palindromic Substrings.md\n\tO(N^2) - None Manacher's Algorithm  \n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def countSubstrings(self, s: str) -> int:  \n        if not s: return 0  \n        rst = len(s)  \n        i = 0  \n        while i < len(s):  \n            j = i  \n            while i+1 < len(s) and s[i] == s[i+1]:  \n                i += 1  \n                rst += i-j  \n            rr = i  \n            while j - 1 >= 0 and i + 1 < len(s) and s[j-1] == s[i+1]:  \n                j -= 1  \n                i += 1  \n                rst += 1  \n            i = rr + 1  \n        return rst  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Palindromic/README.md","path":"List/Palindromic/README.md","topic":"List","section":"Palindromic","title":"Manacher's Algorithm","displayTitle":"Palindromic Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nbTSfrEfo6M"],"markdown":"README.md\nManacher's Algorithm  \n[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nbTSfrEfo6M](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nbTSfrEfo6M)\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/1096._Brace_Expansion_II.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/1096._Brace_Expansion_II.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"1096. Brace Expansion II.md","displayTitle":"1096. Brace Expansion II","problemNumber":1096,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1096. Brace Expansion II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def braceExpansionII(self, expression: str) -> List[str]:  \n        def helper(pattern):  \n            item, items = [''], []  \n            pattern = deque(pattern)  \n            while pattern:  \n                cur = pattern.popleft()  \n                if cur == ',':  \n                    items.append(item)  \n                    item = ['']  \n                else:  \n                    if cur == '{':  \n                        level = 1  \n                        sub_p = ''  \n                        while level:  \n                            sub_p += pattern.popleft()  \n                            if sub_p[-1] == '{': level += 1  \n                            elif sub_p[-1] == '}': level -= 1  \n                        sub_p = sub_p[:-1]  \n                        cur = helper(sub_p)  \n                    else:  \n                        cur = [cur]  \n                    item = [a+b for a in item for b in cur]  \n            else:  \n                items.append(item)  \n            return sorted(set(s for item in items for s in item))  \n        return helper(expression)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/1156._Swap_For_Longest_Repeated_Character_Substring.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/1156._Swap_For_Longest_Repeated_Character_Substring.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"1156. Swap For Longest Repeated Character Substring.md","displayTitle":"1156. Swap For Longest Repeated Character Substring","problemNumber":1156,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1156. Swap For Longest Repeated Character Substring.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maxRepOpt1(self, s: str) -> int:  \n        c_len, size = [[c, len(list(g))] for c, g in itertools.groupby(s)], 1  \n        ret = 0  \n        counter = Counter(c for c, size in c_len)  \n        for i, (c, size) in enumerate(c_len):  \n            ret = max(ret, size+(counter[c]>1))  \n            if i >= 2 and c_len[i-1][1] == 1 and c_len[i-2][0] == c:  \n                if counter[c] > 2:  \n                    ret = max(ret, size + c_len[i-2][1] + 1)  \n                else:  \n                    ret = max(ret, size + c_len[i-2][1])  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/1163._Last_Substring_in_Lexicographical_Order.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/1163._Last_Substring_in_Lexicographical_Order.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"1163. Last Substring in Lexicographical Order.md","displayTitle":"1163. Last Substring in Lexicographical Order","problemNumber":1163,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"1163. Last Substring in Lexicographical Order.md\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/1181._Before_and_After_Puzzle.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/1181._Before_and_After_Puzzle.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"1181. Before and After Puzzle.md","displayTitle":"1181. Before and After Puzzle","problemNumber":1181,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1181. Before and After Puzzle.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def beforeAndAfterPuzzles(self, phrases: List[str]) -> List[str]:  \n        start = defaultdict(list)  \n        for i, p in enumerate(phrases):  \n            words = p.split()  \n            a, b = words[0], ' '.join(words[1:])  \n            start[a].append((i, b))  \n        ret = []  \n        for i, p in enumerate(phrases):  \n            words = p.split()  \n            ret += [(p + (f' {w}' if w else '')) for j, w in start[words[-1]] if i != j]  \n        return sorted(set(ret))            \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/1247._Minimum_Swaps_to_Make_Strings_Equal.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/1247._Minimum_Swaps_to_Make_Strings_Equal.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"1247. Minimum Swaps to Make Strings Equal.md","displayTitle":"1247. Minimum Swaps to Make Strings Equal","problemNumber":1247,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1247. Minimum Swaps to Make Strings Equal.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minimumSwap(self, s1: str, s2: str) -> int:  \n        xy, yx = 0, 0  \n        for a, b in zip(s1, s2):  \n            if a == b: continue  \n            elif a == 'x': xy += 1  \n            else: yx += 1  \n        return -1 if (xy+yx) % 2 else ((xy+yx) // 2 + (xy%2))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/146._LRU_Cache.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/146._LRU_Cache.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"146. LRU Cache.md","displayTitle":"146. LRU Cache","problemNumber":146,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"146. LRU Cache.md\n```python  \nclass Node:  \n    def __init__(self, val=0, prev=None, next=None):  \n        self.val, self.prev, self.next = val, prev, next  \n\n\nclass Dlist:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.head, self.tail = Node(), Node()  \n        self.head.next = self.tail  \n        self.tail.prev = self.head  \n      \n    def appendleft(self, item):  \n        item.next = self.head.next  \n        item.next.prev = item  \n        item.prev = self.head  \n        self.head.next = item  \n      \n    def popitem(self, item):  \n        item.next.prev = item.prev  \n        item.prev.next = item.next  \n      \n    def last(self):  \n        return self.tail.prev  \n          \n          \nclass LRUCache:  \n\n    def __init__(self, capacity: int):  \n        self.list = Dlist()  \n        self.capa = capacity  \n        self.data = {}  \n\n    def get(self, key: int) -> int:  \n        if key not in self.data:  \n            return -1  \n        item, ret = self.data[key]  \n        self.list.popitem(item)  \n        self.list.appendleft(item)  \n        return ret  \n\n    def put(self, key: int, value: int) -> None:  \n        if key in self.data:  \n            self.data[key][1] = value  \n            self.get(key)  \n        else:  \n            item = Node(key)  \n            self.data[key] = [item, value]  \n            self.list.appendleft(item)  \n          \n        if len(self.data) > self.capa:  \n            to_pop_item = self.list.last()  \n            self.list.popitem(to_pop_item)  \n            del self.data[to_pop_item.val]  \n\n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/157._Read_N_Characters_Given_Read4.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/157._Read_N_Characters_Given_Read4.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"157. Read N Characters Given Read4.md","displayTitle":"157. Read N Characters Given Read4","problemNumber":157,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"157. Read N Characters Given Read4.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def read(self, buf, n):  \n        \"\"\"  \n        :type buf: Destination buffer (List[str])  \n        :type n: Number of characters to read (int)  \n        :rtype: The number of actual characters read (int)  \n        \"\"\"  \n        if n <= 0: return 0  \n        for i in range(n)[::4]:  \n            tmp = [0] * 4  \n            size = read4(tmp)  \n            for j in range(size):  \n                buf[i+j] = tmp[j]  \n            if size != 4: break  \n        return min(n, i+size)  \n\n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/158._Read_N_Characters_Given_Read4_II___Call_multiple_times.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/158._Read_N_Characters_Given_Read4_II___Call_multiple_times.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"158. Read N Characters Given Read4 II   Call multiple times.md","displayTitle":"158. Read N Characters Given Read4 II Call multiple times","problemNumber":158,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"158. Read N Characters Given Read4 II   Call multiple times.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.remain = []  \n          \n    def read(self, buf: List[str], n: int) -> int:  \n        while len(self.remain) < n:  \n            tmp = [None] * 4  \n            cnt = read4(tmp)  \n            self.remain.extend(tmp[:cnt])  \n            if cnt < 4:  \n                break  \n        cnt = len(self.remain)  \n        for i in range(min(cnt, n)):  \n            buf[i] = self.remain[i]  \n        self.remain[:n] = []  \n        return min(cnt, n)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/161._One_Edit_Distance.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/161._One_Edit_Distance.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"161. One Edit Distance.md","displayTitle":"161. One Edit Distance","problemNumber":161,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/one-edit-distance/discuss/702870/Python-Concise-Understand-it-in-5-second"],"markdown":"161. One Edit Distance.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/one-edit-distance/discuss/702870/Python-Concise-Understand-it-in-5-second\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/186._Reverse_Words_in_a_String_II.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/186._Reverse_Words_in_a_String_II.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"186. Reverse Words in a String II.md","displayTitle":"186. Reverse Words in a String II","problemNumber":186,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/reverse-words-in-a-string-ii/discuss/715615/Python-Concise-In-place"],"markdown":"186. Reverse Words in a String II.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/reverse-words-in-a-string-ii/discuss/715615/Python-Concise-In-place\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/2._Add_Two_Numbers.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/2._Add_Two_Numbers.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"2. Add Two Numbers.md","displayTitle":"2. Add Two Numbers","problemNumber":2,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"2. Add Two Numbers.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:  \n        ret = ListNode()  \n        c1, c2, cur, carry = l1, l2, ret, False  \n          \n        while c1 or c2:  \n            val = (c1.val if c1 else 0) + (c2.val if c2 else 0) + carry  \n            cur.next, carry = ListNode(val % 10), val // 10  \n            cur = cur.next  \n            c1, c2 = c1.next if c1 else c1, c2.next if c2 else c2  \n        else:  \n            if carry:  \n                cur.next = ListNode(1)  \n          \n        return ret.next  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/249._Group_Shifted_Strings.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/249._Group_Shifted_Strings.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"249. Group Shifted Strings.md","displayTitle":"249. Group Shifted Strings","problemNumber":249,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"249. Group Shifted Strings.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def groupStrings(self, strings: List[str]) -> List[List[str]]:  \n          \n        d = defaultdict(list)  \n        for s in strings:  \n            delta = ord(s[0]) - ord('a')  \n            ss = ''.join(chr(97+((ord(c)-97-delta) % 26)) for c in s)  \n            d[ss].append(s)  \n        return d.values()  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/271._Encode_and_Decode_Strings.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/271._Encode_and_Decode_Strings.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"271. Encode and Decode Strings.md","displayTitle":"271. Encode and Decode Strings","problemNumber":271,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/encode-and-decode-strings/discuss/715649/Python-Straightforward"],"markdown":"271. Encode and Decode Strings.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/encode-and-decode-strings/discuss/715649/Python-Straightforward\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/30._Substring_with_Concatenation_of_All_Words.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/30._Substring_with_Concatenation_of_All_Words.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"30. Substring with Concatenation of All Words.md","displayTitle":"30. Substring with Concatenation of All Words","problemNumber":30,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"30. Substring with Concatenation of All Words.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findSubstring(self, s: str, words: List[str]) -> List[int]:  \n        if not words:  \n            return []  \n        c = Counter(words)  \n        size = len(words[0])  \n        rst = []  \n        for i in range(len(s)+1-size*len(words)):  \n            j, cc = i, c.copy()  \n            while j < i+size*len(words) and s[j:j+size] in c:  \n                cur_w = s[j:j+size]  \n                cc[cur_w] -= 1  \n                if cc[cur_w] < 0:  \n                    break  \n                j += size  \n            if all(v == 0 for v in cc.values()):  \n                rst.append(i)  \n        return rst  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/316._Remove_Duplicate_Letters.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/316._Remove_Duplicate_Letters.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"316. Remove Duplicate Letters.md","displayTitle":"316. Remove Duplicate Letters","problemNumber":316,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"316. Remove Duplicate Letters.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def removeDuplicateLetters(self, s: str) -> str:  \n        ret, start = '', 0  \n        chars = set(s)  \n        while chars:  \n            for c in string.ascii_lowercase:  \n                if c in ret or c not in s: continue  \n                if set(s[s.index(c):]) >= chars:  \n                    ret += c  \n                    chars.remove(c)  \n                    s = s[s.index(c)+1:]  \n                    break  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/415._Add_Strings.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/415._Add_Strings.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"415. Add Strings.md","displayTitle":"415. Add Strings","problemNumber":415,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"415. Add Strings.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def addStrings(self, num1: str, num2: str) -> str:  \n        rst = ''  \n        carry = False  \n        num1, num2 = list(num1), list(num2)  \n        while num1 or num2:  \n            cur = (int(num1.pop()) if num1 else 0) + (int(num2.pop()) if num2 else 0) + carry  \n            rst += str(cur % 10)  \n            carry = cur // 10  \n        if carry:  \n            rst += '1'  \n        return rst[::-1]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/43._Multiply_Strings.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/43._Multiply_Strings.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"43. Multiply Strings.md","displayTitle":"43. Multiply Strings","problemNumber":43,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"43. Multiply Strings.md\n\t\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def multiply(self, num1: str, num2: str) -> str:  \n        if num1 == '0' or num2 == '0': return '0'  \n        num1, num2 = num1[::-1], num2[::-1]  \n        m, n = len(num1), len(num2)  \n        rst = [0] * (m+n)  \n        for i1, v1 in enumerate(num1):  \n            for i2, v2 in enumerate(num2):  \n                rst[i1+i2] += int(v1) * int(v2)  \n                rst[i1+i2+1] += rst[i1+i2] // 10  \n                rst[i1+i2] %= 10  \n        while rst[-1] == 0:  \n            rst.pop()  \n        return ''.join(map(str, rst))[::-1]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/443._String_Compression.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/443._String_Compression.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"443. String Compression.md","displayTitle":"443. String Compression","problemNumber":443,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"443. String Compression.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def compress(self, chars: List[str]) -> int:  \n        idx1, idx2, cnt = 0, 0, 0  \n        chars.append('0')  \n        for i, c in enumerate(chars):  \n            if i != 0 and chars[i] != chars[i-1]:  \n                chars[idx1] = chars[i-1]  \n                idx1 += 1  \n                if cnt == 1:  \n                    continue  \n                for cc in str(cnt):  \n                    chars[idx1] = cc  \n                    idx1 += 1  \n                cnt = 1  \n            else:  \n                cnt += 1  \n                  \n        return idx1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/49._Group_Anagrams.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/49._Group_Anagrams.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"49. Group Anagrams.md","displayTitle":"49. Group Anagrams","problemNumber":49,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/group-anagrams/discuss/681219/Python-Concise-O(N"],"markdown":"49. Group Anagrams.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/group-anagrams/discuss/681219/Python-Concise-O(N)-no-need-to-sort-str\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/522._Longest_Uncommon_Subsequence_II.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/522._Longest_Uncommon_Subsequence_II.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"522. Longest Uncommon Subsequence II.md","displayTitle":"522. Longest Uncommon Subsequence II","problemNumber":522,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"522. Longest Uncommon Subsequence II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findLUSlength(self, strs: List[str]) -> int:  \n        # This is an important technic to check whether a string is a substring of another string  \n        def is_substr(s, ss):  \n            idx = 0  \n            for c in ss:  \n                if idx < len(s) and c == s[idx]:  \n                    idx += 1  \n            return idx == len(s)  \n        strs = sorted(strs, key=lambda x:len(x), reverse=True)  \n        for i, s in enumerate(strs):  \n            if all(not is_substr(s, ss) for j, ss in enumerate(strs) if i != j):  \n                return len(s)  \n        return -1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/537._Complex_Number_Multiplication.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/537._Complex_Number_Multiplication.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"537. Complex Number Multiplication.md","displayTitle":"537. Complex Number Multiplication","problemNumber":537,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/complex-number-multiplication/discuss/702715/Python-Concise-%2B-Straightforward"],"markdown":"537. Complex Number Multiplication.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/complex-number-multiplication/discuss/702715/Python-Concise-%2B-Straightforward\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/539._Minimum_Time_Difference.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/539._Minimum_Time_Difference.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"539. Minimum Time Difference.md","displayTitle":"539. Minimum Time Difference","problemNumber":539,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"539. Minimum Time Difference.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findMinDifference(self, timePoints: List[str]) -> int:  \n        times = sorted(int(time.split(':')[0])*60+int(time.split(':')[1]) for time in timePoints)  \n        times.append(times[0]+60*24)  \n        return min(b-a for a, b in zip(times, times[1:]))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/541._Reverse_String_II.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/541._Reverse_String_II.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"541. Reverse String II.md","displayTitle":"541. Reverse String II","problemNumber":541,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"541. Reverse String II.md\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/557._Reverse_Words_in_a_String_III.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/557._Reverse_Words_in_a_String_III.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"557. Reverse Words in a String III.md","displayTitle":"557. Reverse Words in a String III","problemNumber":557,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"557. Reverse Words in a String III.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def reverseWords(self, s: str) -> str:  \n        return ' '.join(w[::-1] for w in s.split())  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/57._Insert_Interval.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/57._Insert_Interval.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"57. Insert Interval.md","displayTitle":"57. Insert Interval","problemNumber":57,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"57. Insert Interval.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def insert(self, intervals: List[List[int]], newInterval: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:  \n        ret, added = [], False  \n        start, end = newInterval  \n        for l, r in intervals:  \n            if r < start:  \n                ret.append([l, r])  \n            elif end < l:  \n                if not added:  \n                    ret.append(list(newInterval))  \n                    added = True  \n                ret.append([l, r])  \n            else:  \n                if added:  \n                    pl, pr = ret[-1]  \n                    ret[-1] = [min(pl, l), max(pr, r)]  \n                else:  \n                    ret.append([min(start, l), max(end, r)])  \n                    added = True  \n        if not added:  \n            ret.append(list(newInterval))  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/659._Split_Array_into_Consecutive_Subsequences.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/659._Split_Array_into_Consecutive_Subsequences.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"659. Split Array into Consecutive Subsequences.md","displayTitle":"659. Split Array into Consecutive Subsequences","problemNumber":659,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"659. Split Array into Consecutive Subsequences.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isPossible(self, nums: List[int]) -> bool:  \n        tail, req = Counter(), Counter() # defaultdict(int)  \n          \n        for num in nums:  \n            if req[num] > 0:  \n                req[num] -= 1  \n            if tail[num-1]:  \n                tail[num-1] -= 1  \n                tail[num] += 1  \n            else:  \n                tail[num] += 1  \n                req[num+1] += 1  \n                req[num+2] += 1  \n          \n        return all(v == 0 for v in req.values())  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/67._Add_Binary.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/67._Add_Binary.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"67. Add Binary.md","displayTitle":"67. Add Binary","problemNumber":67,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"67. Add Binary.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def addBinary(self, a: str, b: str) -> str:  \n        a, b = list(a), list(b)  \n        carry, rst = False, ''  \n        while a or b:  \n            v1, v2 = int(a.pop()) if a else 0, int(b.pop()) if b else 0  \n            v = v1 + v2 + carry  \n            rst += str(v % 2)  \n            carry = v // 2  \n        if carry:  \n            rst += '1'  \n        return rst[::-1]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/678._Valid_Parenthesis_String.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/678._Valid_Parenthesis_String.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"678. Valid Parenthesis String.md","displayTitle":"678. Valid Parenthesis String","problemNumber":678,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-parenthesis-string/discuss/107570/JavaC%2B%2BPython-One-Pass-Count-the-Open-Parenthesis"],"markdown":"678. Valid Parenthesis String.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/valid-parenthesis-string/discuss/107570/JavaC%2B%2BPython-One-Pass-Count-the-Open-Parenthesis\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/680._Valid_Palindrome_II.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/680._Valid_Palindrome_II.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"680. Valid Palindrome II.md","displayTitle":"680. Valid Palindrome II","problemNumber":680,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-palindrome-ii/discuss/701203/Python-Concise-O(n"],"markdown":"680. Valid Palindrome II.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/valid-palindrome-ii/discuss/701203/Python-Concise-O(n)\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/681._Next_Closest_Time.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/681._Next_Closest_Time.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"681. Next Closest Time.md","displayTitle":"681. Next Closest Time","problemNumber":681,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"681. Next Closest Time.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def nextClosestTime(self, time: str) -> str:  \n        # if cur_minute != max_minute  \n        #.     -> update minute to nxt_minute  \n        # elif cur_hour != max_hour  \n        #.     -> update hour to nxt_hour, update minute to min_minute  \n        # else:  \n        #.     update hour to min_hour, update minute to min_minute  \n        def to_valid(input):  \n            ret = str(input)  \n            if len(ret) == 2:  \n                return ret  \n            return '0' + ret  \n          \n        digits = sorted(list(set(c for c in time if c != ':')))  \n        hour, minute = map(int, time.split(':'))  \n          \n        minutes = []  \n        for i in range(60):  \n            if all(c in digits for c in to_valid(i)):  \n                minutes.append(i)  \n                  \n        hours = []  \n        for i in range(24):  \n            if all(c in digits for c in to_valid(i)):  \n                hours.append(i)  \n          \n        if minute != minutes[-1]:  \n            return to_valid(hour) + ':' + to_valid(minutes[minutes.index(minute)+1])  \n        elif hour != hours[-1]:  \n            return to_valid(hours[hours.index(hour)+1]) + ':' + to_valid(minutes[0])  \n        else:  \n            return to_valid(hours[0]) + ':' + to_valid(minutes[0])  \n          \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/722._Remove_Comments.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/722._Remove_Comments.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"722. Remove Comments.md","displayTitle":"722. Remove Comments","problemNumber":722,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-comments/discuss/702669/Python-line-by-line-O(N"],"markdown":"722. Remove Comments.md\n\t[https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-comments/discuss/702669/Python-line-by-line-O(N)](https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-comments/discuss/702669/Python-line-by-line-O(N))\n\t\n\t\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def removeComments(self, source: List[str]) -> List[str]:  \n        '''  \n        1. in block comment?  \n            yes -> search for end of block comment  \n            no -> search for beginnning of block comment  \n               -> search for beginnning of line comment  \n          \n        '''  \n        ret, in_block, prev, i = [], False, '', 0  \n          \n        while i < len(source):  \n            line = source[i]  \n            if not in_block:  \n                idx_line, idx_block = line.find('//'), line.find('/*')  \n                if idx_line == -1 and idx_block == -1:  \n                    if prev+line:  \n                        ret.append(prev+line)  \n                    prev = ''  \n                    i += 1  \n                elif idx_line == -1 or (idx_block != -1 and idx_block < idx_line):  \n                    prev += line[:idx_block]  \n                    source[i], in_block = line[idx_block+2:], True  \n                else:  \n                    if prev or idx_line != 0:  \n                        ret.append(prev+line[:idx_line])  \n                    prev = ''  \n                    i += 1  \n            else:  \n                idx_end_block = line.find('*/')  \n                if idx_end_block == -1:  \n                    i += 1  \n                else:  \n                    source[i], in_block = line[idx_end_block+2:], False  \n                      \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/767._Reorganize_String.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/767._Reorganize_String.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"767. Reorganize String.md","displayTitle":"767. Reorganize String","problemNumber":767,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"767. Reorganize String.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def reorganizeString(self, S: str) -> str:  \n        rst = []  \n        counter = Counter(S)  \n        order = sorted(counter.keys(), key=lambda x: -counter[x])  \n        idx, size = 0, counter[order[0]]  \n        bucket = [[] for _ in range(size)]  \n        for c in order:  \n            for _ in range(counter[c]):  \n                bucket[idx].append(c)  \n                idx = (idx+1) % size  \n        if size > 1 and len(bucket[size-2]) == 1:  \n            return ''  \n        return ''.join(''.join(b) for b in bucket)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/791._Custom_Sort_String.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/791._Custom_Sort_String.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"791. Custom Sort String.md","displayTitle":"791. Custom Sort String","problemNumber":791,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/custom-sort-string/discuss/702725/Python-Concise-O(N"],"markdown":"791. Custom Sort String.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/custom-sort-string/discuss/702725/Python-Concise-O(N)-%2B-Sort\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/809._Expressive_Words.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/809._Expressive_Words.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"809. Expressive Words.md","displayTitle":"809. Expressive Words","problemNumber":809,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"809. Expressive Words.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def expressiveWords(self, S: str, words: List[str]) -> int:  \n        def condense(s):  \n            p_c, cnt, ret = s[0], 1, []  \n            for c in s[1:]+'$':  \n                if c != p_c:  \n                    ret.append((p_c, cnt))  \n                    p_c, cnt = c, 1  \n                else:  \n                    cnt += 1  \n            return ret  \n                      \n        cond = condense(S)  \n        ret = 0  \n        for word in words:  \n            cond_cur = condense(word)  \n            if len(cond_cur) == len(cond) and all(a[0]==b[0] and (a[1]==b[1] or a[1]>b[1] and a[1]>=3) for a, b in zip(cond, cond_cur)):  \n                ret += 1  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/824._Goat_Latin.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/824._Goat_Latin.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"824. Goat Latin.md","displayTitle":"824. Goat Latin","problemNumber":824,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"824. Goat Latin.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def toGoatLatin(self, S: str) -> str:  \n        words = []  \n        for i, s in enumerate(S.split()):  \n            if s[0].lower() in ['a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u']:  \n                s += 'ma'  \n            else:  \n                s = s[1:]+s[0]+'ma'  \n            s += 'a' * (i+1)  \n            words.append(s)  \n        return ' '.join(words)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/833._Find_And_Replace_in_String.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/833._Find_And_Replace_in_String.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"833. Find And Replace in String.md","displayTitle":"833. Find And Replace in String","problemNumber":833,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"833. Find And Replace in String.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findReplaceString(self, S: str, indexes: List[int], sources: List[str], targets: List[str]) -> str:  \n        ret, cur = '', 0  \n          \n        for idx, u, v in sorted(zip(indexes, sources, targets)):  \n            if cur < idx:  \n                ret += S[cur:idx]  \n                cur = idx  \n              \n            if S[cur:cur+len(u)] == u:  \n                ret += v  \n                cur += len(u)  \n            else:  \n                ...  \n          \n        return ret + S[cur:]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/890._Find_and_Replace_Pattern.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/890._Find_and_Replace_Pattern.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"890. Find and Replace Pattern.md","displayTitle":"890. Find and Replace Pattern","problemNumber":890,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"890. Find and Replace Pattern.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findAndReplacePattern(self, words: List[str], pattern: str) -> List[str]:  \n        def is_valid(word):  \n            if len(word) != len(pattern):  \n                return False  \n            d_12, d_21 = {}, {}  \n            for c1, c2 in zip(word, pattern):  \n                if c1 not in d_12:  \n                    if c2 in d_21:  \n                        return False  \n                    d_12[c1] = c2  \n                    d_21[c2] = c1  \n                elif d_12[c1] != c2:  \n                    return False  \n            return True  \n        rst = []  \n        for word in words:  \n            if is_valid(word):  \n                rst.append(word)  \n        return rst  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/936._Stamping_The_Sequence.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/936._Stamping_The_Sequence.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"936. Stamping The Sequence.md","displayTitle":"936. Stamping The Sequence","problemNumber":936,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"936. Stamping The Sequence.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def movesToStamp(self, s: str, t: str) -> List[int]:  \n        def check(idx):  \n            moved = False  \n            for i in range(m):  \n                if t[idx+i] == '?': continue  \n                if t[idx+i] != s[i]: return False  \n                moved = True  \n            t[idx:idx+m] = ['?'] * m  \n            if moved:  \n                ret.append(idx)  \n            return moved  \n        m, n, ret, s, t = len(s), len(t), [], list(s), list(t)  \n        moved = True  \n        while moved:  \n            moved = False  \n            for i in range(n-m+1):  \n                moved |= check(i)  \n        return ret[::-1] if t == ['?']*n else []  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Pure-programming/README.md","path":"List/Pure-programming/README.md","topic":"List","section":"Pure programming","title":"Pure programming Overview","displayTitle":"Pure programming Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"List/README.md","path":"List/README.md","topic":"List","section":"Overview","title":"> Tricks","displayTitle":"Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n\n> Tricks  \n\n1. `Counter()` can be used to create a `defaultdict(int)`\n\n"},{"id":"List/Sliding-window/Monotone_Stack.md","path":"List/Sliding-window/Monotone_Stack.md","topic":"List","section":"Sliding window","title":"Monotone Stack.md","displayTitle":"Monotone Stack","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":4,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/next-greater-element-iii/discuss/702697/Python-Concise-O(n"],"markdown":"Monotone Stack.md\n\t- 84. Largest Rectangle in Histogram\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def largestRectangleArea(self, heights: List[int]) -> int:  \n        stack = []  \n        rst = 0  \n        for i, height in enumerate(heights + [0]):  \n            idx_prev = i  \n            while stack and stack[-1][1] >= height:  \n                idx_prev, h_prev = stack.pop()  \n                rst = max(rst, (i - idx_prev) * h_prev)  \n            stack.append((idx_prev, height))  \n        return rst  \n```\n\n\t- 85. Maximal Rectangle\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maximalRectangle(self, M: List[List[str]]) -> int:  \n        if not M or not M[0]: return 0  \n        m, n = len(M), len(M[0])  \n        rst = 0  \n        h = [0] * (n+1)  \n        for row in M:  \n            stack = [(0, -1)]  \n            for i, v in enumerate(row+[0]):  \n                if v == '1':  \n                    h[i] += 1  \n                else:  \n                    h[i] = 0  \n                idx = i  \n                while stack and stack[-1][0] > h[i]:  \n                    height, idx = stack.pop()  \n                    rst = max(rst, height * (i-idx))  \n                stack.append((h[i], idx))  \n        return rst  \n```\n\n\t- 1475. Final Prices With a Special Discount in a Shop\n\n\t- 556. Next Greater Element III\n\n\t\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/next-greater-element-iii/discuss/702697/Python-Concise-O(n)\n\n\t- 42. Trapping Rain Water\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def trap(self, height: List[int]) -> int:  \n        stack, ret = [], 0  \n          \n        for i, val in enumerate(height):  \n            while stack and height[stack[-1]] <= val:  \n                if len(stack) >= 2:  \n                    h = min(val, height[stack[-2]]) - height[stack[-1]]  \n                    w = i - stack[-2] - 1  \n                    ret += w * h  \n                stack.pop()  \n            stack.append(i)  \n          \n        return ret  \n```\n\n\t- 654. Maximum Binary Tree\n\n```python  \n# Definition for a binary tree node.  \n# class TreeNode:  \n#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):  \n#         self.val = val  \n#         self.left = left  \n#         self.right = right  \nclass Solution:  \n    def constructMaximumBinaryTree(self, nums: List[int]) -> TreeNode:  \n        '''  \n        # Recursive  \n        if not nums: return None  \n        val = max(nums)  \n        return TreeNode(val, self.constructMaximumBinaryTree(nums[:nums.index(val)]),  \n                             self.constructMaximumBinaryTree(nums[nums.index(val)+1:]))  \n        '''  \n        '''  \n        # Recursive optimized  \n        def dfs(l, r):  \n            if l == r: return None  \n            val = max(nums[l:r])  \n            idx = l + nums[l:r].index(val)  \n            return TreeNode(val, dfs(l, idx), dfs(idx+1, r))  \n        return dfs(0, len(nums))  \n        '''  \n        '''  \n        # Non-recursive  \n        ret = TreeNode()  \n        stack = [((0, len(nums)), (ret, 'l'))]  \n        while stack:  \n            (l, r), (p, dir) = stack.pop()  \n            if l == r: continue  \n            node = TreeNode(max(nums[l:r]))  \n            idx = l + nums[l:r].index(node.val)  \n            if dir == 'l': p.left = node  \n            else: p.right = node  \n              \n            stack.append(((idx+1, r), (node, 'r')))  \n            stack.append(((l, idx), (node, 'l')))  \n        return ret.left  \n        '''  \n        # Optimal  \n        stack = []  \n        for val in nums:  \n            node = TreeNode(val)  \n            left = None  \n            while stack and stack[-1].val < val:  \n                left = stack.pop()  \n            node.left = left  \n            if stack:  \n                stack[-1].right = node  \n            stack.append(node)  \n        return stack[0]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Sliding-window/Monotone_queue.md","path":"List/Sliding-window/Monotone_queue.md","topic":"List","section":"Sliding window","title":"Monotone queue.md","displayTitle":"Monotone queue","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"Monotone queue.md\n\tTo get the max/min value from a moving window\n\n\t- 1438. Longest Continuous Subarray With Absolute Diff Less Than or Equal to Limit\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def longestSubarray(self, nums: List[int], limit: int) -> int:  \n        minStack, maxStack = deque(), deque()  \n        l, ret = 0, 0  \n        for i, num in enumerate(nums):  \n            while minStack and nums[minStack[-1]] >= num:  \n                minStack.pop()  \n            minStack.append(i)  \n            while maxStack and nums[maxStack[-1]] <= num:  \n                maxStack.pop()  \n            maxStack.append(i)  \n            while nums[maxStack[0]] - nums[minStack[0]] > limit:  \n                if minStack[0] == l:  \n                    minStack.popleft()  \n                if maxStack[0] == l:  \n                    maxStack.popleft()  \n                l += 1  \n            ret = max(ret, i-l+1)  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/Sliding-window/README.md","path":"List/Sliding-window/README.md","topic":"List","section":"Sliding window","title":"Maintain a state while sliding window","displayTitle":"Sliding window Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\nMaintain a state while sliding window\n\n"},{"id":"List/Sliding-window/easy.md","path":"List/Sliding-window/easy.md","topic":"List","section":"Sliding window","title":"easy.md","displayTitle":"easy","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":10,"links":[],"markdown":"easy.md\n\t1. Dictionary, Dictionary, Dictionary  \n\t2. Prefix_sum\n\n\t- 3. Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def lengthOfLongestSubstring(self, s: str) -> int:  \n        ret, counter, l = 0, Counter(), 0  \n          \n        for i, c in enumerate(s):  \n            counter[c] += 1  \n              \n            while counter[c] > 1:  \n                counter[s[l]] -= 1  \n                l += 1  \n              \n            ret = max(ret, i-l+1)  \n          \n        return ret  \n```\n\n\t- 1477. Find Two Non-overlapping Sub-arrays Each With Target Sum\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minSumOfLengths(self, arr: List[int], target: int) -> int:  \n        prefix = {0: -1}  \n        best, bests, rst = math.inf, [math.inf] * len(arr), math.inf  \n        cur = 0  \n        for i, v in enumerate(arr):  \n            cur += v  \n            if cur - target in prefix:  \n                begin = prefix[cur-target]  \n                if begin > -1:  \n                    rst = min(rst, i-begin + bests[begin])  \n                best = min(best, i-begin)  \n            bests[i] = best  \n            prefix[cur] = i  \n        return rst if rst != math.inf else -1  \n```  \n\t\t\n\t\tFollowing solution is more straightforward.   \n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minSumOfLengths(self, arr: List[int], target: int) -> int:  \n        size_l, size_r = [math.inf] * len(arr), [math.inf] * len(arr)  \n          \n        l, cur_sum, best = 0, 0, math.inf  \n        for i, num in enumerate(arr):  \n            cur_sum += num  \n            while cur_sum > target:  \n                cur_sum -= arr[l]  \n                l += 1  \n                  \n            if cur_sum == target:  \n                best = min(best, i-l+1)  \n              \n            size_l[i] = best  \n              \n        r, cur_sum, best = len(arr)-1, 0, math.inf  \n        for i in range(len(arr))[::-1]:  \n            while cur_sum > target:  \n                cur_sum -= arr[r]  \n                r -= 1  \n      \n            if cur_sum == target:  \n                best = min(best, r-i)  \n            cur_sum += arr[i]  \n            size_r[i] = best  \n          \n        ret = min(size_l[i]+size_r[i] for i in range(len(arr)))  \n        return ret if ret != math.inf else -1  \n```\n\n\t- 76. Minimum Window Substring\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minWindow(self, s: str, t: str) -> str:  \n        c = Counter(t)  \n        cnt = len(c)  \n        l, r, rst = 0, 0, s+t  \n        while r < len(s) or cnt == 0:  \n            if cnt == 0:  \n                # move l  \n                c[s[l]] += 1  \n                if c[s[l]] == 1:  \n                    cnt += 1  \n                l += 1  \n            else:  \n                # move r  \n                c[s[r]] -= 1  \n                if c[s[r]] == 0:  \n                    cnt -= 1  \n                r += 1  \n            if cnt == 0 and len(s[l:r]) < len(rst):  \n                rst = s[l:r]  \n        return rst if rst != s+t else ''  \n                  \n                      \n```\n\n\t- 159. Longest Substring with At Most Two Distinct Characters\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def lengthOfLongestSubstringTwoDistinct(self, s: str) -> int:  \n        d, cnt, ret = Counter(), 2, 0  \n        for i, c in enumerate(s):  \n            d[c] += 1  \n            if d[c] == 1:  \n                cnt += 1  \n            if len(d) <= 2:  \n                ret += 1  \n            else:  \n                d[s[i-ret]] -= 1  \n                if d[s[i-ret]] == 0:  \n                    del d[s[i-ret]]  \n        return ret  \n\n```\n\n\t- 1358. Number of Substrings Containing All Three Characters\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def numberOfSubstrings(self, s: str) -> int:  \n        ret, d, cnt, l = 0, Counter(), 0, 0  \n        for i, c in enumerate(s):  \n            d[c] += 1  \n            if d[c] == 1: cnt += 1  \n            if cnt == 3:  \n                while d[s[l]] > 1:  \n                    d[s[l]] -= 1  \n                    l += 1  \n                ret += l+1  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n\t- 346. Moving Average from Data Stream\n\n```python  \nclass MovingAverage:  \n\n    def __init__(self, size: int):  \n        self.q = deque()  \n        self.cap = size  \n        self.sum = 0  \n\n    def next(self, val: int) -> float:  \n        self.sum += val  \n        self.q.append(val)  \n          \n        if len(self.q) > self.cap:  \n            self.sum -= self.q.popleft()  \n              \n        return self.sum / len(self.q)  \n```\n\n\t- 1031. Maximum Sum of Two Non-Overlapping Subarrays\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maxSumTwoNoOverlap(self, A: List[int], L: int, M: int) -> int:  \n        def solve(L, M):  \n            s1, s2 = sum(A[:L]), sum(A[L:L+M])  \n            ret, maxS1 = s1+s2, s1  \n            for i in range(L+M, len(A)):  \n                s2 += A[i] - A[i-M]  \n                s1 += A[i-M] - A[i-M-L]  \n                maxS1 = max(maxS1, s1)  \n                ret = max(ret, maxS1+s2)  \n            return ret  \n        return max(solve(L, M), solve(M, L))  \n```\n\n\t- 1423. Maximum Points You Can Obtain from Cards\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def maxScore(self, A: List[int], k: int) -> int:  \n        size = len(A) - k  \n        s = sum(A[:size])  \n        cur = s  \n          \n        for i in range(size, len(A)):  \n            cur += A[i] - A[i-size]  \n            s = min(s, cur)  \n          \n        return sum(A) - s  \n```\n\n\t- 1296. Divide Array in Sets of K Consecutive Numbers\n\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isPossibleDivide(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> bool:  \n        counter = Counter(nums)  \n          \n        for num in sorted(counter.keys()):  \n            cnt = counter[num]  \n            if cnt > 0:  \n                for i in range(k):  \n                    if counter[num+i] < cnt:  \n                        return False  \n                    counter[num+i] -= cnt  \n          \n        return all(v == 0 for v in counter.values())  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/1249._Minimum_Remove_to_Make_Valid_Parentheses.md","path":"List/stack/1249._Minimum_Remove_to_Make_Valid_Parentheses.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"1249. Minimum Remove to Make Valid Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"1249. Minimum Remove to Make Valid Parentheses","problemNumber":1249,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1249. Minimum Remove to Make Valid Parentheses.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minRemoveToMakeValid(self, s: str) -> str:  \n        stack = []  \n        remove = set()  \n        for i, c in enumerate(s):  \n            if c == '(':  \n                stack.append(i)  \n            elif c == ')':  \n                if stack:  \n                    stack.pop()  \n                else:  \n                    remove.add(i)  \n        for i in stack:  \n            remove.add(i)  \n        return ''.join(c for i, c in enumerate(s) if i not in remove)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/20._Valid_Parentheses.md","path":"List/stack/20._Valid_Parentheses.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"20. Valid Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"20. Valid Parentheses","problemNumber":20,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"20. Valid Parentheses.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isValid(self, s: str) -> bool:  \n        stack = []  \n        pairs = {'(': ')', '[': ']', '{': '}'}  \n        for c in s:  \n            if c in ['(', '[', '{']:  \n                stack.append(pairs[c])  \n            else:  \n                if stack and stack[-1] == c:  \n                    stack.pop()  \n                else:  \n                    return False  \n        return not stack  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/227._Basic_Calculator_II.md","path":"List/stack/227._Basic_Calculator_II.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"227. Basic Calculator II.md","displayTitle":"227. Basic Calculator II","problemNumber":227,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"227. Basic Calculator II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def calculate(self, s: str) -> int:  \n        s = s.strip().replace(' ', '')  \n        nums = []  \n        sign, val = '+', 0  \n        for i, c in enumerate(s):  \n            if c.isdigit():  \n                val = val*10 + int(c)  \n            if not c.isdigit() or i == len(s)-1:  \n                if sign == '+':  \n                    nums.append(val)  \n                elif sign == '-':  \n                    nums.append(-val)  \n                elif sign == '*':  \n                    nums.append(nums.pop() * val)  \n                elif sign == '/':  \n                    nums.append(int(nums.pop() / val))  \n                sign = c  \n                val = 0  \n        return sum(nums)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/388._Longest_Absolute_File_Path.md","path":"List/stack/388._Longest_Absolute_File_Path.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"388. Longest Absolute File Path.md","displayTitle":"388. Longest Absolute File Path","problemNumber":388,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"388. Longest Absolute File Path.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def lengthLongestPath(self, input: str) -> int:  \n        ret, stack, cur = 0, [], 0  \n          \n        for line in input.split('\\n'):  \n            depth = line.count('\\t')  \n            pattern = line.lstrip('\\t')  \n              \n            while depth < len(stack):  \n                cur -= len(stack.pop()) + 1  \n              \n            if '.' in line:  \n                ret = max(ret, cur + len(pattern))  \n            else:  \n                stack.append(pattern)  \n                cur += 1 + len(pattern)  \n              \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/844._Backspace_String_Compare.md","path":"List/stack/844._Backspace_String_Compare.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"844. Backspace String Compare.md","displayTitle":"844. Backspace String Compare","problemNumber":844,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"844. Backspace String Compare.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def backspaceCompare(self, S: str, T: str) -> bool:  \n        s, t = [], []  \n        for c in S:  \n            if c == '#':  \n                if s:  \n                    s.pop()  \n            else:  \n                s.append(c)  \n        for c in T:  \n            if c == '#':  \n                if t:  \n                    t.pop()  \n            else:  \n                t.append(c)  \n        return s == t  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/856._Score_of_Parentheses.md","path":"List/stack/856._Score_of_Parentheses.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"856. Score of Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"856. Score of Parentheses","problemNumber":856,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/score-of-parentheses/discuss/141777/C%2B%2BJavaPython-O(1"],"markdown":"856. Score of Parentheses.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/score-of-parentheses/discuss/141777/C%2B%2BJavaPython-O(1)-Space\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/946._Validate_Stack_Sequences.md","path":"List/stack/946._Validate_Stack_Sequences.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"946. Validate Stack Sequences.md","displayTitle":"946. Validate Stack Sequences","problemNumber":946,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"946. Validate Stack Sequences.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def validateStackSequences(self, pushed: List[int], popped: List[int]) -> bool:  \n        dq = deque(pushed)  \n        stack = []  \n        for val in popped:  \n            if stack and stack[-1] == val:  \n                stack.pop()  \n            else:  \n                while dq:  \n                    stack.append(dq.popleft())  \n                    if stack[-1] == val:  \n                        break  \n                if stack[-1] != val:  \n                    return False  \n                stack.pop()  \n        return not dq and not stack  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"List/stack/README.md","path":"List/stack/README.md","topic":"List","section":"stack","title":"[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stack_(abstract_data_type)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stack_(abstract_data_type))","displayTitle":"stack Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stack_(abstract_data_type"],"markdown":"README.md\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stack_(abstract_data_type)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stack_(abstract_data_type))\n\nO(1) to push and pop at end.\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/102._Binary_Tree_Level_Order_Traversal.md","path":"Tree/BFS/102._Binary_Tree_Level_Order_Traversal.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"102. Binary Tree Level Order Traversal.md","displayTitle":"102. Binary Tree Level Order Traversal","problemNumber":102,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"102. Binary Tree Level Order Traversal.md\n```python  \n# Definition for a binary tree node.  \n# class TreeNode:  \n#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):  \n#         self.val = val  \n#         self.left = left  \n#         self.right = right  \nclass Solution:  \n    def levelOrder(self, root: TreeNode) -> List[List[int]]:  \n        if not root: return []  \n        '''  \n        ret, level, q, nq = [], [], deque([root]), deque()  \n        while q:  \n            cur = q.popleft()  \n            level.append(cur.val)  \n              \n            if cur.left: nq.append(cur.left)  \n            if cur.right: nq.append(cur.right)  \n              \n            if not q:  \n                q, nq = nq, deque()  \n                ret.append(level)  \n                level = []  \n        return ret  \n        '''  \n        ret, level, q, cnt = [], [], deque([root]), 1  \n        while q:  \n            cur = q.popleft()  \n            level.append(cur.val)  \n            cnt -= 1  \n              \n            if cur.left: q.append(cur.left)  \n            if cur.right: q.append(cur.right)  \n              \n            if cnt == 0:  \n                ret.append(level)  \n                level, cnt = [], len(q)  \n                  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/126._Word_Ladder_II.md","path":"Tree/BFS/126._Word_Ladder_II.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"126. Word Ladder II.md","displayTitle":"126. Word Ladder II","problemNumber":126,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/word-ladder-ii/discuss/269012/Python-BFS%2BBacktrack-Greatly-Improved-by-bi-directional-BFS"],"markdown":"126. Word Ladder II.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/word-ladder-ii/discuss/269012/Python-BFS%2BBacktrack-Greatly-Improved-by-bi-directional-BFS\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/1293._Shortest_Path_in_a_Grid_with_Obstacles_Elimination.md","path":"Tree/BFS/1293._Shortest_Path_in_a_Grid_with_Obstacles_Elimination.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"1293. Shortest Path in a Grid with Obstacles Elimination.md","displayTitle":"1293. Shortest Path in a Grid with Obstacles Elimination","problemNumber":1293,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1293. Shortest Path in a Grid with Obstacles Elimination.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def shortestPath(self, grid: List[List[int]], k: int) -> int:  \n        if not grid:  \n            return -1  \n        m, n = len(grid), len(grid[0])  \n        visited = defaultdict(int)  \n\n        q, nq, step = deque([(0, 0, k)]), deque(), 0  \n          \n        while q:  \n            x, y, chance = q.popleft()  \n              \n            if (x, y) == (m-1, n-1):  \n                return step  \n              \n            for dx, dy in [(0, 1), (0, -1), (1, 0), (-1, 0)]:  \n                xx, yy = x+dx, y+dy  \n                if 0 <= xx < m and 0 <= yy < n:  \n                    chance_left = chance - grid[xx][yy]  \n                    if chance_left < 0: continue  \n                    if (xx, yy) not in visited or visited[(xx,yy)] < chance_left:  \n                        visited[(xx, yy)] = chance_left  \n                        nq.append((xx, yy, chance_left))  \n              \n            if not q:  \n                q, nq = nq, deque()  \n                step += 1  \n          \n        return -1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/1345._Jump_Game_IV.md","path":"Tree/BFS/1345._Jump_Game_IV.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"1345. Jump Game IV.md","displayTitle":"1345. Jump Game IV","problemNumber":1345,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1345. Jump Game IV.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minJumps(self, arr: List[int]) -> int:  \n        # BFS  \n        q, nq, visited, move = deque([0]), deque(), set([0]), 0  \n        val2idx = defaultdict(list)  \n          \n        for i, val in enumerate(arr):  \n            val2idx[val].append(i)  \n              \n        while q:  \n            cur = q.popleft()  \n            if cur == len(arr)-1:  \n                return move  \n              \n            for nxt in [cur-1, cur+1] + val2idx[arr[cur]]:  \n                if (not 0 <= nxt < len(arr)) or nxt in visited: continue  \n                nq.append(nxt)  \n                visited.add(nxt)  \n              \n            val2idx[arr[cur]] = []  \n            if not q:  \n                q, nq = nq, q  \n                move += 1  \n          \n        return None  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/1368._Minimum_Cost_to_Make_at_Least_One_Valid_Path_in_a_Grid.md","path":"Tree/BFS/1368._Minimum_Cost_to_Make_at_Least_One_Valid_Path_in_a_Grid.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"1368. Minimum Cost to Make at Least One Valid Path in a Grid.md","displayTitle":"1368. Minimum Cost to Make at Least One Valid Path in a Grid","problemNumber":1368,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"1368. Minimum Cost to Make at Least One Valid Path in a Grid.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/1376._Time_Needed_to_Inform_All_Employees.md","path":"Tree/BFS/1376._Time_Needed_to_Inform_All_Employees.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"1376. Time Needed to Inform All Employees.md","displayTitle":"1376. Time Needed to Inform All Employees","problemNumber":1376,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1376. Time Needed to Inform All Employees.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def numOfMinutes(self, n: int, headID: int, manager: List[int], informTime: List[int]) -> int:  \n        q, ret = deque([(headID, 0)]), 0  \n          \n        graph = defaultdict(set)  \n        for i, val in enumerate(manager):  \n            graph[val].add(i)  \n          \n        while q:  \n            cur, now = q.popleft()  \n            ret = max(ret, now)  \n              \n            for nxt in graph[cur]:  \n                q.append((nxt, now+informTime[cur]))  \n                  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/199._Binary_Tree_Right_Side_View.md","path":"Tree/BFS/199._Binary_Tree_Right_Side_View.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"199. Binary Tree Right Side View.md","displayTitle":"199. Binary Tree Right Side View","problemNumber":199,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"199. Binary Tree Right Side View.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def rightSideView(self, root: TreeNode) -> List[int]:  \n        if not root: return []  \n        q, nq, ret = deque([root]), deque(), [root.val]  \n        while q:  \n            cur = q.popleft()  \n            if cur.left: nq.append(cur.left)  \n            if cur.right: nq.append(cur.right)  \n              \n            if not q and nq:  \n                ret.append(nq[-1].val)  \n                q, nq = nq, deque()  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/279._Perfect_Squares.md","path":"Tree/BFS/279._Perfect_Squares.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"279. Perfect Squares.md","displayTitle":"279. Perfect Squares","problemNumber":279,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"279. Perfect Squares.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def numSquares(self, n: int) -> int:  \n        if n <= 2: return n  \n        square_table = [i*i for i in range(1, int(n**0.5)+1)]  \n        q, nq = [n], []  \n        rst = 0  \n        while q:  \n            rst += 1  \n            for x in q:  \n                for i in square_table:  \n                    if i == x:  \n                        return rst  \n                    elif i > x:  \n                        break  \n                    nq.append(x-i)  \n            q, nq = nq, []  \n        return rst  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/301._Remove_Invalid_Parentheses.md","path":"Tree/BFS/301._Remove_Invalid_Parentheses.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"301. Remove Invalid Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"301. Remove Invalid Parentheses","problemNumber":301,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"301. Remove Invalid Parentheses.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/752._Open_the_Lock.md","path":"Tree/BFS/752._Open_the_Lock.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"752. Open the Lock.md","displayTitle":"752. Open the Lock","problemNumber":752,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"752. Open the Lock.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def openLock(self, deadends: List[str], target: str) -> int:  \n        if '0000' in deadends: return -1  \n        deadends = set(deadends)  \n        q, nq, visited, step = deque(['0000']), deque(), set(['0000']), 0  \n          \n        while q:  \n            cur = q.popleft()  \n            if cur == target:  \n                return step  \n                  \n            for i in range(len(cur)):  \n                val = int(cur[i])  \n                for k in [(val-1)%10, (val+1)%10]:  \n                    nxt = cur[:i] + str(k) + cur[i+1:]  \n                    if nxt in deadends or nxt in visited: continue  \n                    nq.append(nxt)  \n                    visited.add(nxt)  \n              \n            if not q:  \n                q, nq = nq, deque()  \n                step += 1  \n          \n        return -1            \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/785._Is_Graph_Bipartite?.md","path":"Tree/BFS/785._Is_Graph_Bipartite?.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"785. Is Graph Bipartite?.md","displayTitle":"785. Is Graph Bipartite?","problemNumber":785,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"785. Is Graph Bipartite?.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isBipartite(self, graph: List[List[int]]) -> bool:  \n        '''  \n        # DFS  \n        sides = {}  \n        def dfs(u):  \n            if u not in sides:  \n                sides[u] = 0  \n            for v in graph[u]:  \n                if v in sides:  \n                    if sides[v] == sides[u]:  \n                        return False  \n                    continue  \n                sides[v] = 1 - sides[u]  \n                if not dfs(v):  \n                    return False  \n            return True  \n        return all(dfs(i) for i in range(len(graph)))  \n        '''  \n        # BFS  \n        def bfs(u):  \n            sides = {u: 0}  \n            q = deque([u])  \n            while q:  \n                u = q.pop()  \n                for v in graph[u]:  \n                    if v in sides:  \n                        if sides[v] == sides[u]:  \n                            return False  \n                        continue  \n                    sides[v] = 1 - sides[u]  \n                    q.append(v)  \n            return True  \n        return all(bfs(u) for u in range(len(graph)))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/841._Keys_and_Rooms.md","path":"Tree/BFS/841._Keys_and_Rooms.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"841. Keys and Rooms.md","displayTitle":"841. Keys and Rooms","problemNumber":841,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"841. Keys and Rooms.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def canVisitAllRooms(self, rooms: List[List[int]]) -> bool:  \n        q = [0]  \n        visited = set()  \n        while q:  \n            u = q.pop()  \n            visited.add(u)  \n            for v in rooms[u]:  \n                if v not in visited:  \n                    q.append(v)  \n          \n        return len(visited) == len(rooms)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/854._K_Similar_Strings.md","path":"Tree/BFS/854._K_Similar_Strings.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"854. K Similar Strings.md","displayTitle":"854. K Similar Strings","problemNumber":854,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"854. K Similar Strings.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def kSimilarity(self, A: str, B: str) -> int:  \n        def neis(s):  \n            i = 0  \n            while s[i] == B[i]: i+= 1  \n            ret = []  \n            for j in range(i+1, len(A)):  \n                if s[j] == B[i]:  \n                    cur = list(s)  \n                    cur[i], cur[j] = cur[j], cur[i]  \n                    yield ''.join(cur)  \n        q, visited = [(A, 0)], set()  \n        for cand, move in q:  \n            if cand == B: return move  \n            for nei in neis(cand):  \n                if nei not in visited:  \n                    visited.add(nei), q.append((nei, move+1))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/BFS/README.md","path":"Tree/BFS/README.md","topic":"Tree","section":"BFS","title":"BFS Overview","displayTitle":"BFS Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/1505._Minimum_Possible_Integer_After_at_Most_K_Adjacent_Swaps_On_Digits.md","path":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/1505._Minimum_Possible_Integer_After_at_Most_K_Adjacent_Swaps_On_Digits.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Binary Index Tree","title":"1505. Minimum Possible Integer After at Most K Adjacent Swaps On Digits.md","displayTitle":"1505. Minimum Possible Integer After at Most K Adjacent Swaps On Digits","problemNumber":1505,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"1505. Minimum Possible Integer After at Most K Adjacent Swaps On Digits.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/218._The_Skyline_Problem.md","path":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/218._The_Skyline_Problem.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Binary Index Tree","title":"218. The Skyline Problem.md","displayTitle":"218. The Skyline Problem","problemNumber":218,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"218. The Skyline Problem.md\n```python  \nfrom sortedcontainers import SortedList  \n\nclass Solution:  \n    def getSkyline(self, buildings: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int]]:  \n        heights = [0] * len(buildings) * 2  \n        for i, (l, r, h) in enumerate(buildings):  \n            heights[i*2] = (l, 0, -h) # add  \n            heights[i*2+1] = (r, 1, h) # remove  \n        heights = sorted(heights)  \n          \n        ret, hs = [(-1, -math.inf)], SortedList([0])  \n        for idx, side, h in heights:  \n            if side == 0:  \n                hs.add(-h)  \n            else:  \n                hs.remove(h)  \n              \n            if hs[-1] != ret[-1][1]:  \n                ret.append((idx, hs[-1]))  \n        return ret[1:]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/307._Range_Sum_Query___Mutable.md","path":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/307._Range_Sum_Query___Mutable.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Binary Index Tree","title":"307. Range Sum Query   Mutable.md","displayTitle":"307. Range Sum Query Mutable","problemNumber":307,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"307. Range Sum Query   Mutable.md\n```python  \nclass BIT:  \n    def __init__(self, size):  \n        self.arr = [0] * (size+1)  \n          \n    def sum(self, x):  \n        x += 1  \n        ret = 0  \n        while x:  \n            ret += self.arr[x]  \n            x -= x & (-x)  \n        return ret  \n      \n    def update(self, x, delta):  \n        x += 1  \n        while x < len(self.arr):  \n            self.arr[x] += delta  \n            x += x & (-x)  \n\nclass NumArray:  \n\n    def __init__(self, nums: List[int]):  \n        self.nums = nums  \n        self.bit = BIT(len(nums))  \n        for i, num in enumerate(nums):  \n            self.bit.update(i, num)  \n\n    def update(self, i: int, val: int) -> None:  \n        self.bit.update(i, val - self.nums[i])  \n        self.nums[i] = val  \n\n    def sumRange(self, i: int, j: int) -> int:  \n        return self.bit.sum(j) - self.bit.sum(i-1)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/315._Count_of_Smaller_Numbers_After_Self.md","path":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/315._Count_of_Smaller_Numbers_After_Self.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Binary Index Tree","title":"315. Count of Smaller Numbers After Self.md","displayTitle":"315. Count of Smaller Numbers After Self","problemNumber":315,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":2,"links":[],"markdown":"315. Count of Smaller Numbers After Self.md\n```python  \nfrom sortedcontainers import SortedList  \nclass Solution:  \n    def countSmaller(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:  \n        vals = SortedList()  \n        ret = [None] * len(nums)  \n        for i in range(len(nums))[::-1]:  \n            val = nums[i]  \n            idx = vals.bisect_left(val)  \n            ret[i] = idx  \n            vals.add(val)  \n        return ret  \n```  \n\t\n```python  \nclass BIT:  \n    def __init__(self, size):  \n        self.arr = [0] * size  \n      \n    def add(self, x, delta):  \n        while x < len(self.arr):  \n            self.arr[x] += delta  \n            x += x & (-x)  \n\n    def sum(self, x):  \n        ret = 0  \n        while x:  \n            ret += self.arr[x]  \n            x -= x & (-x)  \n        return ret  \n              \n\nclass Solution:  \n    def countSmaller(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:  \n        if not nums: return []  \n        counter = Counter(nums)  \n        rank = {}  \n        for i, val in enumerate(sorted(counter.keys()), 1):  \n            rank[val] = i  \n        bit = BIT(len(rank))  \n        ret = [None] * len(nums)  \n        for i in range(len(nums))[::-1]:  \n            val = nums[i]  \n            ret[i] = bit.sum(rank[val]-1)  \n            bit.add(rank[val], 1)  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/README.md","path":"Tree/Binary-Index-Tree/README.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Binary Index Tree","title":"> Wikipedia: A Fenwick tree or binary indexed tree is a data structure that can efficiently update elements and calculate prefix sums in a table of numbers.","displayTitle":"Binary Index Tree Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n> Wikipedia: A Fenwick tree or binary indexed tree is a data structure that can efficiently update elements and calculate prefix sums in a table of numbers.  \n\n> note  \n0. **Index 0 is discarded in BIT**  \n1. BIT can be used to calculate prefix-sum  \n2. As an extension of #1, BIT can be used for range sum query. Aka RSQ  \n3. It can be used to track the number of value greater/smaller values.  \n    Segment Tree, SortedList (multiset), Balanced Tree can achieve similar goal  \n    See [315. Count of Smaller Numbers After Self]() for details on this point  \n\n```python  \nclass BIT:  \n    def __init__(self, size):  \n        self.arr = [0] * (size+1)  \n          \n    def sum(self, x):  \n        x += 1  \n        ret = 0  \n        while x:  \n            ret += self.arr[x]  \n            x -= x & (-x)  \n        return ret  \n      \n    def update(self, x, delta):  \n        x += 1  \n        while x < len(self.arr):  \n            self.arr[x] += delta  \n            x += x & (-x)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Binary-Lifting/5456._Kth_Ancestor_of_a_Tree_Node.md","path":"Tree/Binary-Lifting/5456._Kth_Ancestor_of_a_Tree_Node.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Binary Lifting","title":"5456. Kth Ancestor of a Tree Node.md","displayTitle":"5456. Kth Ancestor of a Tree Node","problemNumber":5456,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"5456. Kth Ancestor of a Tree Node.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/Binary-Lifting/README.md","path":"Tree/Binary-Lifting/README.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Binary Lifting","title":"Binary Lifting Overview","displayTitle":"Binary Lifting Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/100._Same_Tree.md","path":"Tree/DFS/100._Same_Tree.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"100. Same Tree.md","displayTitle":"100. Same Tree","problemNumber":100,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"100. Same Tree.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isSameTree(self, p: TreeNode, q: TreeNode) -> bool:  \n        '''  \n        # Recursive: Time O(N) Space O(N)  \n        if not p and not q: return True  \n        if not (p and q and p.val == q.val): return False  \n        return self.isSameTree(p.left, q.left) and self.isSameTree(p.right, q.right)  \n        '''  \n        # Non-recursive: Time O(N) Space O(N)  \n        stack = []  \n        while p or q or stack:  \n            while p or q:  \n                if not ((p and q) and p.val == q.val): return False  \n                stack.append((p.right, q.right))  \n                p, q = p.left, q.left  \n            p, q = stack.pop()  \n        return True  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/101._Symmetric_Tree.md","path":"Tree/DFS/101._Symmetric_Tree.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"101. Symmetric Tree.md","displayTitle":"101. Symmetric Tree","problemNumber":101,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"101. Symmetric Tree.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def isSymmetric(self, root: TreeNode) -> bool:  \n        '''  \n        # Recursive  \n        def dfs(a, b):  \n            if ((a is None) ^ ( b is None)) or (a and a.val != b.val): return False  \n            if not a: return True  \n            return dfs(a.left, b.right) and dfs(a.right, b.left)  \n        return dfs(root.left, root.right) if root else True  \n        '''  \n        # Non-recursive  \n        if not root: return True  \n        stack = [(root.left, root.right)]  \n        while stack:  \n            a, b = stack.pop()  \n            if (a is None) ^ (b is None): return False  \n            if a and a.val != b.val: return False  \n            if not a: continue  \n              \n            stack.append((a.left, b.right))  \n            stack.append((a.right, b.left))  \n        return True  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/105._Construct_Binary_Tree_from_Preorder_and_Inorder_Traversal.md","path":"Tree/DFS/105._Construct_Binary_Tree_from_Preorder_and_Inorder_Traversal.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"105. Construct Binary Tree from Preorder and Inorder Traversal.md","displayTitle":"105. Construct Binary Tree from Preorder and Inorder Traversal","problemNumber":105,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/construct-binary-tree-from-preorder-and-inorder-traversal/discuss/719653/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Optimized-recursive-%2B-Non-recursive"],"markdown":"105. Construct Binary Tree from Preorder and Inorder Traversal.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/construct-binary-tree-from-preorder-and-inorder-traversal/discuss/719653/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Optimized-recursive-%2B-Non-recursive\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/108._Convert_Sorted_Array_to_Binary_Search_Tree.md","path":"Tree/DFS/108._Convert_Sorted_Array_to_Binary_Search_Tree.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"108. Convert Sorted Array to Binary Search Tree.md","displayTitle":"108. Convert Sorted Array to Binary Search Tree","problemNumber":108,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/convert-sorted-array-to-binary-search-tree/discuss/719416/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive"],"markdown":"108. Convert Sorted Array to Binary Search Tree.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/convert-sorted-array-to-binary-search-tree/discuss/719416/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/110._Balanced_Binary_Tree.md","path":"Tree/DFS/110._Balanced_Binary_Tree.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"110. Balanced Binary Tree.md","displayTitle":"110. Balanced Binary Tree","problemNumber":110,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/balanced-binary-tree/discuss/721706/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive"],"markdown":"110. Balanced Binary Tree.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/balanced-binary-tree/discuss/721706/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/1110._Delete_Nodes_And_Return_Forest.md","path":"Tree/DFS/1110._Delete_Nodes_And_Return_Forest.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"1110. Delete Nodes And Return Forest.md","displayTitle":"1110. Delete Nodes And Return Forest","problemNumber":1110,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1110. Delete Nodes And Return Forest.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def delNodes(self, root: TreeNode, to_delete: List[int]) -> List[TreeNode]:  \n        ret = []  \n        def dfs(cur, p):  \n            if not cur: return  \n            if cur.val in to_delete:  \n                if p and p.left == cur:  \n                    p.left = None  \n                if p and p.right == cur:  \n                    p.right = None  \n                if cur.left and cur.left.val not in to_delete:  \n                    ret.append(cur.left)  \n                if cur.right and cur.right.val not in to_delete:  \n                    ret.append(cur.right)  \n            dfs(cur.right, cur)  \n            dfs(cur.left, cur)  \n\n              \n        dfs(root, None)  \n        if root and root.val not in to_delete:  \n            ret.append(root)  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/113._Path_Sum_II.md","path":"Tree/DFS/113._Path_Sum_II.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"113. Path Sum II.md","displayTitle":"113. Path Sum II","problemNumber":113,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"113. Path Sum II.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/1462._Course_Schedule_IV.md","path":"Tree/DFS/1462._Course_Schedule_IV.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"1462. Course Schedule IV.md","displayTitle":"1462. Course Schedule IV","problemNumber":1462,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1462. Course Schedule IV.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def checkIfPrerequisite(self, n: int, E: List[List[int]], queries: List[List[int]]) -> List[bool]:  \n        pred = defaultdict(set)  \n        for u, v in E:  \n            pred[v].add(u)  \n        indirect_pred = deepcopy(pred)  \n        visited = set()  \n        def dfs(u):  \n            visited.add(u)  \n            for v in pred[u]:  \n                if v not in visited:  \n                    dfs(v)  \n                indirect_pred[u] |= indirect_pred[v]  \n        for i in range(n):  \n            dfs(i)  \n\n        return [u in indirect_pred[v] for u, v in queries]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/173._Binary_Search_Tree_Iterator.md","path":"Tree/DFS/173._Binary_Search_Tree_Iterator.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"173. Binary Search Tree Iterator.md","displayTitle":"173. Binary Search Tree Iterator","problemNumber":173,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"173. Binary Search Tree Iterator.md\n```python  \n# Definition for a binary tree node.  \n# class TreeNode:  \n#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):  \n#         self.val = val  \n#         self.left = left  \n#         self.right = right  \nclass BSTIterator:  \n\n    def __init__(self, root: TreeNode):  \n        self.stack = []  \n        self._next(root)  \n          \n    def _next(self, node):  \n        while node:  \n            self.stack.append(node)  \n            node = node.left  \n\n    def next(self) -> int:  \n        \"\"\"  \n        @return the next smallest number  \n        \"\"\"  \n        node = self.stack.pop()  \n        self._next(node.right)  \n        return node.val  \n\n\n    def hasNext(self) -> bool:  \n        \"\"\"  \n        @return whether we have a next smallest number  \n        \"\"\"  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/22._Generate_Parentheses.md","path":"Tree/DFS/22._Generate_Parentheses.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"22. Generate Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"22. Generate Parentheses","problemNumber":22,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"22. Generate Parentheses.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def generateParenthesis(self, n: int) -> List[str]:  \n        def dfs(l, r, s):  \n            if not l and not r:  \n                rst.append(s)  \n                return  \n            if l:  \n                dfs(l-1, r, s+'(')  \n            if l < r:  \n                dfs(l, r-1, s+')')  \n        rst = []  \n        dfs(n, n, '')  \n        return rst  \n\n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/241._Different_Ways_to_Add_Parentheses.md","path":"Tree/DFS/241._Different_Ways_to_Add_Parentheses.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"241. Different Ways to Add Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"241. Different Ways to Add Parentheses","problemNumber":241,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"241. Different Ways to Add Parentheses.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def diffWaysToCompute(self, input: str) -> List[int]:  \n        # a b c  \n        # (a b) c  \n        # a (b c)  \n        patterns = []  \n        i = 0  \n        while i < len(input):  \n            if not input[i].isdigit():  \n                patterns.append(input[i])  \n                i += 1  \n            else:  \n                j = i  \n                while j < len(input) and input[j].isdigit(): j += 1  \n                patterns.append(int(input[i:j]))  \n                i = j  \n        def cal(vl, op, vr):  \n            if op == '+': return vl+vr  \n            elif op == '-': return vl-vr  \n            elif op == '*': return vl*vr  \n            else:  \n                return None  \n        def get_vals(vl, op1, val, op2, vr):  \n            return [cal(cal(vl, op1, val), op2, vr), cal(vl, op1, cal(val, op2, vr))]  \n        def dfs(l, r):  \n            if r-l == 1: return [patterns[l]]  \n            else:  \n                ret = []  \n                for i in range(l+1, r, 2):  \n                    for vl in dfs(l, i):  \n                        for vr in dfs(i+1, r):  \n                            ret.append(cal(vl, patterns[i], vr))  \n            return ret  \n        return dfs(0, len(patterns))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/297._Serialize_and_Deserialize_Binary_Tree.md","path":"Tree/DFS/297._Serialize_and_Deserialize_Binary_Tree.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"297. Serialize and Deserialize Binary Tree.md","displayTitle":"297. Serialize and Deserialize Binary Tree","problemNumber":297,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/serialize-and-deserialize-binary-tree/discuss/719519/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive"],"markdown":"297. Serialize and Deserialize Binary Tree.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/serialize-and-deserialize-binary-tree/discuss/719519/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/301._Remove_Invalid_Parentheses.md","path":"Tree/DFS/301._Remove_Invalid_Parentheses.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"301. Remove Invalid Parentheses.md","displayTitle":"301. Remove Invalid Parentheses","problemNumber":301,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"301. Remove Invalid Parentheses.md\n\tDFS is simple. It is only the matter of how many unnecessary subtree we can cut.  \n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def removeInvalidParentheses(self, s: str) -> List[str]:  \n        # BFS Time: 2^N Space: 2^N  \n            l = 0  \n            for c in s:  \n                if c == '(':  \n                    l += 1  \n                elif c == ')':  \n                    l -= 1  \n                if l < 0: return False  \n            return l == 0  \n        q, nq = [(s, 0)], []  \n        rst = []  \n        while q:  \n            for cur in q:  \n                if is_valid(cur[0]):  \n                    rst.append(cur[0])  \n                else:  \n                    s, cur_idx = cur  \n                    for i in range(cur_idx, len(s)):  \n                        if i == cur_idx or s[i-1] != s[i]:  \n                            nq.append((s[:i]+s[i+1:], i))      \n            if rst:  \n                break  \n            q, nq = nq, []  \n        return rst  \n\n        '''  \n        # DFS Time: 2^N Space N  \n        rm_l, rm_r = 0, 0  \n        for c in s:  \n            if c == '(':  \n                rm_l += 1  \n            elif c == ')':  \n                if rm_l > 0:  \n                    rm_l -= 1  \n                else:  \n                    rm_r += 1  \n        def dfs(cur, idx, rm_l, rm_r, l):  \n            if idx == len(s) or rm_l < 0 or rm_r < 0 or l < 0:  \n                if rm_l == 0 and rm_r == 0 and l == 0:  \n                    rst.add(cur)  \n                return  \n            if s[idx] == '(':  \n                dfs(cur, idx+1, rm_l-1, rm_r, l)  \n                dfs(cur+s[idx], idx+1, rm_l, rm_r, l+1)  \n            elif s[idx] == ')':  \n                dfs(cur, idx+1, rm_l, rm_r-1, l)  \n                dfs(cur+s[idx], idx+1, rm_l, rm_r, l-1)  \n            else:  \n                dfs(cur+s[idx], idx+1, rm_l, rm_r, l)  \n        rst = set()  \n        dfs('', 0, rm_l, rm_r, 0)  \n        return list(rst) if rst else [\"\"]  \n        '''  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/337._House_Robber_III.md","path":"Tree/DFS/337._House_Robber_III.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"337. House Robber III.md","displayTitle":"337. House Robber III","problemNumber":337,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"337. House Robber III.md\n```python  \n# Definition for a binary tree node.  \n# class TreeNode:  \n#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):  \n#         self.val = val  \n#         self.left = left  \n#         self.right = right  \nclass Solution:  \n    def rob(self, root: TreeNode) -> int:  \n          \n        def dp(cur):  \n            if not cur:  \n                return (0, 0)  \n              \n            ls, ln = dp(cur.left)  \n            rs, rn = dp(cur.right)  \n              \n            return (cur.val + ln + rn, max(ls, ln) + max(rs, rn))  \n          \n        return max(dp(root))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/426._Convert_Binary_Search_Tree_to_Sorted_Doubly_Linked_List.md","path":"Tree/DFS/426._Convert_Binary_Search_Tree_to_Sorted_Doubly_Linked_List.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"426. Convert Binary Search Tree to Sorted Doubly Linked List.md","displayTitle":"426. Convert Binary Search Tree to Sorted Doubly Linked List","problemNumber":426,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"426. Convert Binary Search Tree to Sorted Doubly Linked List.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def treeToDoublyList(self, root: 'Node') -> 'Node':  \n        if not root: return None  \n        def dfs(cur):  \n            if not cur.left and not cur.right: return cur, cur  \n            if cur.left:  \n                ll, lr = dfs(cur.left)  \n                lr.right, cur.left = cur, lr  \n            else:  \n                ll, lr = cur, cur  \n            if cur.right:  \n                rl, rr = dfs(cur.right)  \n                rl.left, cur.right = cur, rl  \n            else:  \n                rl, rr = cur, cur  \n            return ll, rr  \n        ll, rr = dfs(root)  \n        ll.left, rr.right = rr, ll  \n        return ll  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/437._Path_Sum_III.md","path":"Tree/DFS/437._Path_Sum_III.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"437. Path Sum III.md","displayTitle":"437. Path Sum III","problemNumber":437,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/path-sum-iii/discuss/721966/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive"],"markdown":"437. Path Sum III.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/path-sum-iii/discuss/721966/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/489._Robot_Room_Cleaner.md","path":"Tree/DFS/489._Robot_Room_Cleaner.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"489. Robot Room Cleaner.md","displayTitle":"489. Robot Room Cleaner","problemNumber":489,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"489. Robot Room Cleaner.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/606._Construct_String_from_Binary_Tree.md","path":"Tree/DFS/606._Construct_String_from_Binary_Tree.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"606. Construct String from Binary Tree.md","displayTitle":"606. Construct String from Binary Tree","problemNumber":606,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"606. Construct String from Binary Tree.md\n```python  \n# Definition for a binary tree node.  \n# class TreeNode:  \n#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):  \n#         self.val = val  \n#         self.left = left  \n#         self.right = right  \nclass Solution:  \n    def tree2str(self, t: TreeNode) -> str:  \n        if t == None:  \n            return ''  \n        l, r = self.tree2str(t.left), self.tree2str(t.right)  \n        return f'{t.val}' + (f'({l})' if l or r else '') + (f'({r})' if r else '')        \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/617._Merge_Two_Binary_Trees.md","path":"Tree/DFS/617._Merge_Two_Binary_Trees.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"617. Merge Two Binary Trees.md","displayTitle":"617. Merge Two Binary Trees","problemNumber":617,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/merge-two-binary-trees/discuss/718497/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive"],"markdown":"617. Merge Two Binary Trees.md\n\thttps://leetcode.com/problems/merge-two-binary-trees/discuss/718497/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/996._Number_of_Squareful_Arrays.md","path":"Tree/DFS/996._Number_of_Squareful_Arrays.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"996. Number of Squareful Arrays.md","displayTitle":"996. Number of Squareful Arrays","problemNumber":996,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"996. Number of Squareful Arrays.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def numSquarefulPerms(self, A: List[int]) -> int:  \n        c = Counter(A)  \n        cand = {x: [y for y in c if (int((x+y)**0.5))**2 == (x+y)] for x in c}  \n        print(cand)  \n        def dfs(x, size=1):  \n            if size == len(A): return 1  \n            c[x] -= 1  \n            ret = sum(dfs(y, size+1) for y in cand[x] if c[y])  \n            c[x] += 1  \n            return ret  \n        return sum(map(dfs, c))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/DFS/README.md","path":"Tree/DFS/README.md","topic":"Tree","section":"DFS","title":"DFS Overview","displayTitle":"DFS Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n"},{"id":"Tree/README.md","path":"Tree/README.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Overview","title":"Recursive! Recursive! Recursive!","displayTitle":"Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/balanced-binary-tree/discuss/721706/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive","https://leetcode.com/problems/construct-binary-tree-from-preorder-and-inorder-traversal/discuss/719653/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Optimized-recursive-%2B-Non-recursive","https://leetcode.com/problems/convert-sorted-array-to-binary-search-tree/discuss/719416/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive","https://leetcode.com/problems/distribute-coins-in-binary-tree/discuss/719810/Python-Concise-Anyone-has-interest-in-non-recursive-implementation","https://leetcode.com/problems/flatten-binary-tree-to-linked-list/discuss/721737/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive","https://leetcode.com/problems/lowest-common-ancestor-of-a-binary-tree/discuss/721668/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive","https://leetcode.com/problems/path-sum-iii/discuss/721966/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive","https://leetcode.com/problems/serialize-and-deserialize-binary-tree/discuss/719519/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive","https://yonglife.com/2019/05/04/binary-tree-traversal-updated/"],"markdown":"README.md\nRecursive! Recursive! Recursive!  \n\n> pre/in/post order traversal   \nhttps://yonglife.com/2019/05/04/binary-tree-traversal-updated/\n\n> Recursive to Non-recursive   \n\n- [437. Path Sum III]([https://leetcode.com/problems/path-sum-iii/discuss/721966/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive](https://leetcode.com/problems/path-sum-iii/discuss/721966/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive))\n- [236. Lowest Common Ancestor of a Binary Tree](https://leetcode.com/problems/lowest-common-ancestor-of-a-binary-tree/discuss/721668/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive)  \n- [979. Distribute Coins in Binary Tree]([https://leetcode.com/problems/distribute-coins-in-binary-tree/discuss/719810/Python-Concise-Anyone-has-interest-in-non-recursive-implementation](https://leetcode.com/problems/distribute-coins-in-binary-tree/discuss/719810/Python-Concise-Anyone-has-interest-in-non-recursive-implementation))\n- [297. Serialize and Deserialize Binary Tree](https://leetcode.com/problems/serialize-and-deserialize-binary-tree/discuss/719519/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive)  \n- [108. Convert Sorted Array to Binary Search Tree](https://leetcode.com/problems/convert-sorted-array-to-binary-search-tree/discuss/719416/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive)  \n- [105. Construct Binary Tree from Preorder and Inorder Traversal](https://leetcode.com/problems/construct-binary-tree-from-preorder-and-inorder-traversal/discuss/719653/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Optimized-recursive-%2B-Non-recursive)  \n- [110. Balanced Binary Tree]([https://leetcode.com/problems/balanced-binary-tree/discuss/721706/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive](https://leetcode.com/problems/balanced-binary-tree/discuss/721706/python-concise-recursive-non-recursive))\n- [114. Flatten Binary Tree to Linked List](https://leetcode.com/problems/flatten-binary-tree-to-linked-list/discuss/721737/Python-Concise-Recursive-%2B-Non-recursive)\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Segment-Tree/307._Range_Sum_Query___Mutable.md","path":"Tree/Segment-Tree/307._Range_Sum_Query___Mutable.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Segment Tree","title":"307. Range Sum Query   Mutable.md","displayTitle":"307. Range Sum Query Mutable","problemNumber":307,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"307. Range Sum Query   Mutable.md\n```python  \nclass STree:  \n    def __init__(self, nums):  \n        if not nums: return  \n        self.nums = nums  \n        self.arr = [0] * len(nums) * 4  \n        self.size = len(nums)  \n        self._build(0, nums, 0, len(nums)-1)  \n      \n    def _build(self, sidx, nums, l, r):  \n        if l == r:  \n            self.arr[sidx] = nums[l]  \n            return nums[l]  \n        mid = (l+r) // 2  \n        val = sum([self._build(sidx*2+1, nums, l    , mid),  \n                   self._build(sidx*2+2, nums, mid+1, r  )])  \n        self.arr[sidx] = val  \n        return val  \n\n    def sum(self, l, r):  \n        return self._sum(0, 0, self.size-1, l, r)  \n      \n    def _sum(self, sidx, sl, sr, l, r):  \n        if l <= sl <= sr <= r:  \n            return self.arr[sidx]  \n        elif sr < l or r < sl:  \n            return 0  \n        mid = (sl+sr) // 2  \n        return sum([self._sum(sidx*2+1, sl   , mid, l, r),   \n                    self._sum(sidx*2+2, mid+1, sr , l, r)])  \n\n    def update(self, idx, delta):  \n        self._update(0, 0, self.size-1, idx, delta)  \n      \n    def _update(self, sidx, sl, sr, idx, delta):  \n        if sr < idx or idx < sl:  \n            return  \n\n        self.arr[sidx] += delta  \n        if sl == sr: return  \n        mid = (sl+sr) // 2  \n        self._update(sidx*2+1, sl   , mid, idx, delta)  \n        self._update(sidx*2+2, mid+1, sr , idx, delta)  \n          \nclass NumArray:  \n\n    def __init__(self, nums: List[int]):  \n        self.nums = nums  \n        self.stree = STree(nums)  \n\n    def update(self, i: int, val: int) -> None:  \n        self.stree.update(i, val - self.nums[i])  \n        self.nums[i] = val  \n\n    def sumRange(self, i: int, j: int) -> int:  \n        return self.stree.sum(i, j)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Segment-Tree/README.md","path":"Tree/Segment-Tree/README.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Segment Tree","title":"class STree:","displayTitle":"Segment Tree Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n```python  \nclass STree:  \n    def __init__(self, nums):  \n        if not nums: return  \n        self.nums = nums  \n        self.arr = [0] * len(nums) * 4  \n        self.size = len(nums)  \n        self._build(0, nums, 0, len(nums)-1)  \n      \n    def _build(self, sidx, nums, l, r):  \n        if l == r:  \n            self.arr[sidx] = nums[l]  \n            return nums[l]  \n        mid = (l+r) // 2  \n        val = sum([self._build(sidx*2+1, nums, l    , mid),  \n                   self._build(sidx*2+2, nums, mid+1, r  )])  \n        self.arr[sidx] = val  \n        return val  \n\n    def sum(self, l, r):  \n        return self._sum(0, 0, self.size-1, l, r)  \n      \n    def _sum(self, sidx, sl, sr, l, r):  \n        if l <= sl <= sr <= r:  \n            return self.arr[sidx]  \n        elif sr < l or r < sl:  \n            return 0  \n        mid = (sl+sr) // 2  \n        return sum([self._sum(sidx*2+1, sl   , mid, l, r),   \n                    self._sum(sidx*2+2, mid+1, sr , l, r)])  \n\n    def update(self, idx, delta):  \n        self._update(0, 0, self.size-1, idx, delta)  \n      \n    def _update(self, sidx, sl, sr, idx, delta):  \n        if sr < idx or idx < sl:  \n            return  \n\n        self.arr[sidx] += delta  \n        if sl == sr: return  \n        mid = (sl+sr) // 2  \n        self._update(sidx*2+1, sl   , mid, idx, delta)  \n        self._update(sidx*2+2, mid+1, sr , idx, delta)  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/1023._Camelcase_Matching.md","path":"Tree/Trie/1023._Camelcase_Matching.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"1023. Camelcase Matching.md","displayTitle":"1023. Camelcase Matching","problemNumber":1023,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1023. Camelcase Matching.md\n```python  \nclass TreeNode:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.word, self.next = None, defaultdict(TreeNode)  \n\nclass Trie:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.root = TreeNode()  \n      \n    def add(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        cur.word = word  \n      \n    def search(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            if c not in cur.next:  \n                if c.lower() != c: return False  \n            else:  \n                cur = cur.next[c]  \n        return bool(cur.word)  \n              \nclass Solution:  \n    def camelMatch(self, queries: List[str], pattern: str) -> List[bool]:  \n        ret, trie = [], Trie()  \n        trie.add(pattern)  \n        for q in queries:  \n            ret.append(trie.search(q))  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/1065._Index_Pairs_of_a_String.md","path":"Tree/Trie/1065._Index_Pairs_of_a_String.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"1065. Index Pairs of a String.md","displayTitle":"1065. Index Pairs of a String","problemNumber":1065,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1065. Index Pairs of a String.md\n```python  \nclass TreeNode:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.word = None  \n        self.next = defaultdict(TreeNode)  \n\nclass Trie:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.root = TreeNode()  \n      \n    def add(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        cur.word = word       \n\nclass Solution:  \n    def indexPairs(self, text: str, words: List[str]) -> List[List[int]]:  \n        trie = Trie()  \n        for word in words:  \n            trie.add(word)  \n        ret = []  \n        for i in range(len(text)):  \n            cur = trie.root  \n            j = i  \n            while j < len(text):  \n                if text[j] not in cur.next: break   \n                cur = cur.next[text[j]]  \n                if cur.word: ret.append([i, j])  \n                j += 1  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/1268._Search_Suggestions_System.md","path":"Tree/Trie/1268._Search_Suggestions_System.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"1268. Search Suggestions System.md","displayTitle":"1268. Search Suggestions System","problemNumber":1268,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"1268. Search Suggestions System.md\n```python  \nclass Node:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.words = []  \n        self.next = defaultdict(Node)  \nclass Solution:  \n    def suggestedProducts(self, products: List[str], searchWord: str) -> List[List[str]]:  \n        products = sorted(products)  \n        tries = Node()  \n        for product in products:  \n            cur = tries  \n            for c in product:  \n                cur = cur.next[c]  \n                cur.words.append(product)  \n        ret, cur = [], tries  \n        for c in searchWord:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n            ret.append(cur.words[:3])  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/208._Implement_Trie_(Prefix_Tree).md","path":"Tree/Trie/208._Implement_Trie_(Prefix_Tree).md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"208. Implement Trie (Prefix Tree).md","displayTitle":"208. Implement Trie (Prefix Tree)","problemNumber":208,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"208. Implement Trie (Prefix Tree).md\n```python  \nclass TreeNode:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.word = None  \n        self.next = defaultdict(TreeNode)  \n          \nclass Trie:  \n\n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.root = TreeNode()  \n          \n\n    def insert(self, word: str) -> None:  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        cur.word = word  \n          \n\n    def search(self, word: str) -> bool:  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            if c not in cur.next: return False  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        return cur.word  \n          \n          \n\n    def startsWith(self, prefix: str) -> bool:  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in prefix:  \n            if c not in cur.next: return False  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        return True  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/425._Word_Squares.md","path":"Tree/Trie/425._Word_Squares.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"425. Word Squares.md","displayTitle":"425. Word Squares","problemNumber":425,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"425. Word Squares.md\n```python  \nclass TreeNode:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.words = []  \n        self.next = defaultdict(TreeNode)  \n          \nclass Trie:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.root = TreeNode()  \n      \n    def add(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n            cur.words.append(word)  \n          \n    def search(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        return cur.words  \n\nclass Solution:  \n    def wordSquares(self, words: List[str]) -> List[List[str]]:  \n        def dfs(seq):  \n            if len(seq) == len(seq[0]):   \n                ret.append(list(seq))  \n                return  \n            idx = len(seq)  \n            for cand in trie.search(''.join(row[idx] for row in seq)):  \n                seq.append(cand)  \n                dfs(seq)  \n                seq.pop()  \n                  \n        trie, ret = Trie(), []  \n        for w in words:  \n            trie.add(w)  \n          \n        for i, w in enumerate(words):  \n            seq = [w]  \n            dfs(seq)  \n        return ret  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/648._Replace_Words.md","path":"Tree/Trie/648._Replace_Words.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"648. Replace Words.md","displayTitle":"648. Replace Words","problemNumber":648,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"648. Replace Words.md\n```python  \nclass Trie:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        T = lambda: defaultdict(T)  \n        self.root = T()  \n      \n    def add(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur[c]  \n        cur['$'] = word  \n\n    def replace(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            if '$' in cur: return cur['$']  \n            if c not in cur: return word  \n            cur = cur[c]  \n        return word  \n          \nclass Solution:  \n    def replaceWords(self, words: List[str], sentence: str) -> str:  \n        trie = Trie()  \n        for w in words:  \n            trie.add(w)  \n        return ' '.join(trie.replace(word) for word in sentence.split())        \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/745._Prefix_and_Suffix_Search.md","path":"Tree/Trie/745._Prefix_and_Suffix_Search.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"745. Prefix and Suffix Search.md","displayTitle":"745. Prefix and Suffix Search","problemNumber":745,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"745. Prefix and Suffix Search.md\n```python  \nclass TreeNode:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.words = set()  \n        self.next = defaultdict(TreeNode)  \n\nclass Trie:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.root = TreeNode()  \n      \n    def add(self, word, reversed=False):  \n        cur, val = self.root, word if not reversed else word[::-1]  \n        cur.words.add(val)  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n            cur.words.add(val)  \n              \n    def search(self, word):  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            if c not in cur.next: return set()  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        return cur.words  \n          \nclass WordFilter:  \n\n    def __init__(self, words: List[str]):  \n        self.pre, self.post = Trie(), Trie()  \n        self.weight = {word: i for i, word in enumerate(words)}  \n        for w in words:  \n            self.pre.add(w)  \n            self.post.add(w[::-1], reversed=True)  \n\n    def f(self, prefix: str, suffix: str) -> int:  \n        cands = list(self.pre.search(prefix) & self.post.search(suffix[::-1]))  \n        cands = sorted(cands, key = lambda x: self.weight[x])  \n          \n        return self.weight[cands[-1]] if cands else -1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Tree/Trie/README.md","path":"Tree/Trie/README.md","topic":"Tree","section":"Trie","title":"> Typical implementation","displayTitle":"Trie Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n> Typical implementation  \n```python  \nclass TreeNode:  \n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.word = None  \n        self.next = defaultdict(TreeNode)  \n          \nclass Trie:  \n\n    def __init__(self):  \n        self.root = TreeNode()  \n          \n    def insert(self, word: str) -> None:  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        cur.word = word  \n          \n\n    def search(self, word: str) -> bool:  \n        cur = self.root  \n        for c in word:  \n            if c not in cur.next: return False  \n            cur = cur.next[c]  \n        return cur.word  \n```  \n\n> Note  \n\n1. Consider build trie in reversed order if the characters are given in reversed order.\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/1168._Optimize_Water_Distribution_in_a_Village.md","path":"Union-find/1168._Optimize_Water_Distribution_in_a_Village.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"1168. Optimize Water Distribution in a Village.md","displayTitle":"1168. Optimize Water Distribution in a Village","problemNumber":1168,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/optimize-water-distribution-in-a-village/discuss/365853/C%2B%2BPythonJava-Hidden-Well-in-House-0"],"markdown":"1168. Optimize Water Distribution in a Village.md\n[https://leetcode.com/problems/optimize-water-distribution-in-a-village/discuss/365853/C%2B%2BPythonJava-Hidden-Well-in-House-0](https://leetcode.com/problems/optimize-water-distribution-in-a-village/discuss/365853/C%2B%2BPythonJava-Hidden-Well-in-House-0)\n\n\n```  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minCostToSupplyWater(self, n: int, wells: List[int], pipes: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        '''  \n        wells = [(c, 0, i) for i, c in enumerate(wells, 1)]  \n        pipes = [(c, u, v) for u, v, c in pipes]  \n          \n        ret, cnt = 0, 0  \n        # Kruskal   \n        uf = {}  \n        def find(x):  \n            uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n            if uf[x] != x: uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n            return uf[x]  \n        for c, u, v in sorted(wells+pipes):  \n            pu, pv = find(u), find(v)  \n            if pu != pv:  \n                uf[pu] = uf[pv]  \n                ret += c  \n                cnt += 1  \n            if cnt == n:  \n                return ret   \n        '''  \n        # Prim  \n        graph = defaultdict(dict)  \n        for u, v, c in pipes + [(0, i, c) for i, c in enumerate(wells, 1)]:  \n            graph[u][v] = min(c, graph[u].get(v, c))  \n            graph[v][u] = min(c, graph[v].get(u, c))  \n\n        visited, ret = set(), 0  \n        pq = [(0, -1, 0)]  \n        while pq:  \n            c, _, u = heapq.heappop(pq)  \n            if u in visited: continue  \n            ret += c  \n            visited.add(u)  \n            if len(visited) == n+1: return ret  \n            for v, c in graph[u].items():  \n                if v in visited: continue  \n                heapq.heappush(pq, (c, u, v))  \n              \n                  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/128._Longest_Consecutive_Sequence.md","path":"Union-find/128._Longest_Consecutive_Sequence.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"128. Longest Consecutive Sequence.md","displayTitle":"128. Longest Consecutive Sequence","problemNumber":128,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"128. Longest Consecutive Sequence.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def longestConsecutive(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:  \n        d = {num: num for num in nums}  \n        def find(x):  \n            if d[x] - 1 in d: d[x] = find(d[x] - 1)  \n            return d[x]  \n        ret = 0  \n        for num in nums:  \n            ret = max(ret, num - find(num) + 1)  \n        return   \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/200._Number_of_Islands.md","path":"Union-find/200._Number_of_Islands.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"200. Number of Islands.md","displayTitle":"200. Number of Islands","problemNumber":200,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"200. Number of Islands.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def numIslands(self, grid: List[List[str]]) -> int:  \n        def bfs(ori_r, ori_c):  \n            q = deque([(ori_r, ori_c)])  \n              \n            while q:  \n                r, c = q.popleft()  \n                  \n                for x, y in [(-1, 0), (1, 0), (0, 1), (0, -1)]:  \n                    rr, cc = r+x, c+y  \n                    if 0 <= rr < m and 0 <= cc < n and grid[rr][cc] == '1' and (rr, cc) not in visited:  \n                        visited.add((rr, cc))  \n                        q.append((rr, cc))  \n              \n        if not grid or not grid[0]:  \n            return 0  \n        m, n, ret, visited = len(grid), len(grid[0]), 0, set()  \n          \n        for i, row in enumerate(grid):  \n            for j, val in enumerate(row):  \n                if val == '1' and (i, j) not in visited:  \n                    ret += 1  \n                    visited.add((i, j))  \n                    bfs(i, j)  \n                      \n        return ret  \n          \n        '''  \n        uf = {}  \n          \n        def find(x):  \n            uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n            if uf[x] != x: uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n            return uf[x]  \n          \n        def union(x, y): # x-> y  \n            uf[find(x)] = find(y)  \n          \n        for i, row in enumerate(grid):  \n            for j, val in enumerate(row):  \n                if val == '1':  \n                    find((i, j))  \n                    if i>0 and grid[i-1][j] == '1':  \n                        union((i, j), (i-1, j))  \n                    if j>0 and grid[i][j-1] == '1':  \n                        union((i, j), (i, j-1))  \n          \n        return len(set(map(find, uf.keys())))  \n        '''  \n        '''  \n        def dfs(r, c):  \n            for x, y in [(-1, 0), (1, 0), (0, 1), (0, -1)]:  \n                rr, cc = r+x, c+y  \n                if 0 <= rr < m and 0 <= cc < n and grid[rr][cc] == '1' and (rr, cc) not in visited:  \n                    visited.add((rr, cc))  \n                    dfs(rr, cc)  \n              \n        if not grid or not grid[0]:  \n            return 0  \n        m, n, ret, visited = len(grid), len(grid[0]), 0, set()  \n          \n        for i, row in enumerate(grid):  \n            for j, val in enumerate(row):  \n                if val == '1' and (i, j) not in visited:  \n                    ret += 1  \n                    visited.add((i, j))  \n                    dfs(i, j)  \n                      \n        return ret  \n        '''  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/261._Graph_Valid_Tree.md","path":"Union-find/261._Graph_Valid_Tree.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"261. Graph Valid Tree.md","displayTitle":"261. Graph Valid Tree","problemNumber":261,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"261. Graph Valid Tree.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def validTree(self, n: int, edges: List[List[int]]) -> bool:  \n        # What is a tree  \n        # 1. No cycle  \n        # 2. All vertex are connected  \n        uf = {}  \n        def find(x):  \n            uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n            if uf[x] != x: uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n            return uf[x]  \n        def union(x, y):  \n            uf[find(x)] = uf[find(y)]  \n          \n        for u, v in edges:  \n            if find(u) == find(v):  \n                return False  \n            union(u, v)  \n        return True and len(set(map(find, range(n)))) == 1  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/323._Number_of_Connected_Components_in_an_Undirected_Graph.md","path":"Union-find/323._Number_of_Connected_Components_in_an_Undirected_Graph.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"323. Number of Connected Components in an Undirected Graph.md","displayTitle":"323. Number of Connected Components in an Undirected Graph","problemNumber":323,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"323. Number of Connected Components in an Undirected Graph.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def countComponents(self, n: int, edges: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        uf = {}  \n        def find(x):  \n            uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n            if uf[x] != x: uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n            return uf[x]  \n        def union(x, y):  \n            uf[find(x)] = uf[find(y)]  \n          \n        for u, v in edges:  \n            union(u,v)  \n        return len(set(map(find, range(n))))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/399._Evaluate_Division.md","path":"Union-find/399._Evaluate_Division.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"399. Evaluate Division.md","displayTitle":"399. Evaluate Division","problemNumber":399,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"399. Evaluate Division.md\n```python  \n        uf = {}  \n        def find(x):  \n            uf.setdefault(x, (x, 1))  \n            if uf[x][0] != x:  \n                p, r = find(uf[x][0])  \n                uf[x] = (p, r*uf[x][1])  \n            return uf[x]  \n          \n        def union(x, y, ratio): # x -> y  \n            px, rx, py, ry = *find(x), *find(y)  \n            if ratio is None:  \n                return rx / ry if px == py else -1  \n            uf[px] = (py, ratio * (ry / rx))  \n              \n        graph = defaultdict(dict)  \n        for (u, v), w in zip(equations, values):  \n            union(u, v, w)  \n          \n        return [union(u, v, None) if u in uf and v in uf else -1 for u, v in queries]  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/547._Friend_Circles.md","path":"Union-find/547._Friend_Circles.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"547. Friend Circles.md","displayTitle":"547. Friend Circles","problemNumber":547,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"547. Friend Circles.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def findCircleNum(self, M: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        n = len(M)  \n        arr = [i for i in range(n)]  \n        def find(x):  \n            if arr[x] != arr[arr[x]]: arr[x] = find(arr[x])  \n            return arr[x]  \n        for i, row in enumerate(M):  \n            for j, c in enumerate(row):  \n                if c == 1:  \n                    arr[find(i)] = arr[find(j)]  \n        return len(set(map(find, arr)))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/765._Couples_Holding_Hands.md","path":"Union-find/765._Couples_Holding_Hands.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"765. Couples Holding Hands.md","displayTitle":"765. Couples Holding Hands","problemNumber":765,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":false,"codeBlocks":0,"links":["https://leetcode.com/problems/couples-holding-hands/discuss/336706/The-general-mathematical-idea%3A-permutation-graph-and-graph-decomposition"],"markdown":"765. Couples Holding Hands.md\nhttps://leetcode.com/problems/couples-holding-hands/discuss/336706/The-general-mathematical-idea%3A-permutation-graph-and-graph-decomposition.\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/928._Minimize_Malware_Spread_II.md","path":"Union-find/928._Minimize_Malware_Spread_II.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"928. Minimize Malware Spread II.md","displayTitle":"928. Minimize Malware Spread II","problemNumber":928,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"928. Minimize Malware Spread II.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def minMalwareSpread(self, graph: List[List[int]], initial: List[int]) -> int:  \n        def find(x):  \n            nonlocal uf  \n            uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n            if uf[x] != x: uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n            return uf[x]  \n        def union(x, y):  \n            uf[find(x)] = uf[find(y)]  \n              \n        initial.sort(reverse=True)  \n        ret, safe = None, 0  \n        for removed in initial:  \n            uf = {}  \n            for u, row in enumerate(graph):  \n                for v, state in enumerate(row):  \n                    if removed not in [u, v] and state == 1:  \n                        union(u, v)  \n              \n            subset_safe = {s: True for s in set(uf.values())}  \n            subset_cnt = Counter()  \n            for u in range(len(graph)):  \n                if u != removed:  \n                    subset_cnt[find(u)] += 1  \n            for u in initial:  \n                if u != removed:  \n                    subset_safe[find(u)] = False  \n              \n            safe_cnt = sum(val for key, val in subset_cnt.items() if subset_safe[key])  \n\n            if safe_cnt >= safe:  \n                safe, ret = safe_cnt, removed  \n        return ret  \n                  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/947._Most_Stones_Removed_with_Same_Row_or_Column.md","path":"Union-find/947._Most_Stones_Removed_with_Same_Row_or_Column.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"947. Most Stones Removed with Same Row or Column.md","displayTitle":"947. Most Stones Removed with Same Row or Column","problemNumber":947,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"947. Most Stones Removed with Same Row or Column.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def removeStones(self, stones: List[List[int]]) -> int:  \n        uf = {}  \n        def find(x):  \n            if x != uf[x]:  \n                uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n            return uf[x]  \n        def union(a, b):  \n            uf.setdefault(a, a)  \n            uf.setdefault(b, b)  \n            uf[find(a)] = uf[find(b)]  \n          \n        for x, y in stones:  \n            union(x, ~y)  \n        return len(stones) - len(set(map(find , uf)))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/959._Regions_Cut_By_Slashes.md","path":"Union-find/959._Regions_Cut_By_Slashes.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"959. Regions Cut By Slashes.md","displayTitle":"959. Regions Cut By Slashes","problemNumber":959,"isOverview":false,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"959. Regions Cut By Slashes.md\n```python  \nclass Solution:  \n    def regionsBySlashes(self, M: List[str]) -> int:  \n        def find(x):  \n            if arr[x] != arr[arr[x]]: arr[x] = find(arr[x])  \n            return arr[x]  \n        def get_idx(x, y, z):  \n            return x * 2 * n + y * 2 + z  \n        n = len(M)  \n        arr = [i for i in range(n*n*2)]  \n\n        for i in range(n):  \n            for j in range(n):  \n                if M[i][j] == '/':  \n                    if i > 0:  \n                        arr[get_idx(i, j, 0)] = find(get_idx(i-1, j, 0 if M[i-1][j] == '\\\\' else 1))  \n                    if j > 0:  \n                        arr[find(get_idx(i, j, 0))] = find(get_idx(i, j-1, 1))  \n                elif M[i][j] == '\\\\':  \n                    if j > 0:  \n                        arr[find(get_idx(i, j, 0))] = find(get_idx(i, j-1, 1))  \n                    if i > 0:  \n                        arr[get_idx(i, j, 1)] = find(get_idx(i-1, j, 0 if M[i-1][j] == '\\\\' else 1))  \n                else:  \n                    arr[get_idx(i, j, 1)] = arr[get_idx(i, j, 0)]  \n                    if i > 0:  \n                        arr[get_idx(i, j, 0)] = find(get_idx(i-1, j, 0 if M[i-1][j] == '\\\\' else 1))  \n                    if j > 0:  \n                        arr[find(get_idx(i, j, 0))] = find(get_idx(i, j-1, 1))  \n\n\n        return len(set(map(find, arr)))  \n```\n\n"},{"id":"Union-find/README.md","path":"Union-find/README.md","topic":"Union find","section":"Overview","title":"> Implementation","displayTitle":"Overview","problemNumber":null,"isOverview":true,"hasCode":true,"codeBlocks":1,"links":[],"markdown":"README.md\n> Implementation  \n\nTips:   \nCreate uf as list can be faster but dictionary can tell us whether an element is registered in the union-find which is useful in some case.  \n```python  \nuf = {}  \ndef find(x):  \n    uf.setdefault(x, x)  \n    if x != uf[x]:  \n        uf[x] = find(uf[x])  \n    return uf[x]  \ndef union(x, y):  \n    uf[find(x)] = uf[find(y)]  \n```  \n\n> Usage  \n\n>> Count the size of each subcomponent in a graph.   \n1. Do a typical union find to bucket each vertex  \n2. Traverse all vertex and increment the counter of subset it belong to (aka return value of find())  \n\n>> Find cycle in a graph  \n1. Do a typical union find  \n2. A cycle is found when we encounter an edge (u, v) where find(u) == find(v)  \n\n"}]};
